image_desc: Photo by Fatimah Mahmud on August 31, 2020.
text:
ORGAN DLM BADAN
.
Usus merupakan organ penting dalam badan.
.
Usus yg tidak dijaga dgn baik akan menyebabkan toksin berkumpul di dalam nya dan mendatangkan masaalah.
.
Oleh itu jaga lah usus kita.. berikan makanan yg baik2 pd cells2 dlm badan kita supaya usus kita pun terpelihara
.
Makanan terbaik tuu mcmana?
🔰Tinggi nutrisi
🔰Tidak berlemak
🔰GI rendah
🔰Rendah gula
.
Selain diet yg sihat, banyak lagi ilmu yg kita bole dpt bila join Group-Coaching ini.
.
JOM join Sept Intake program, kita kurus dgn pemakanan sihat, tak akan cengkung tapi tetap anggun.

text:
🌈Sun shining through the curtains as you wake. A soft rain falling. Leaf buds opening to spring. A cuckoo calling. Here’s happiness. 🌈 Eversince we started working from home, I now prefer cloudy or light drizzling weather to hot sunny afternoons! As much as I miss face-to-face interactions with my colleagues and friends, I have somehow grown so used to the current lifestyle. I wonder if I will get used to the daily commuting (standing on train) to office, late dinners, insufficient sleep etc. 🤣 For now, let’s all enjoy the work life balance and whatever life throws at us now. ❤️ Today I made baked luncheon meat fries packed in prata skin! 🤩 And I didn’t want to waste the egg wash so I made shredded fried eggs too. 😋😋😋 Oh I tried to create a wooden table texture with my chocolate syrup but not that obvious. 🤣Happy Monday and happy week! 🌻🌻🌻

image_desc: Photo shared by 🍀🌻🌸Juewee🌸🌻🍀 on August 31, 2020 tagging @upzcycl3d. May be an image of 2 people.
text:
🌻You have not lived a perfect day, even though you have earned your money, unless you have done something for someone who will never be able to repay you. 🌻 Giving is not easy but is very fulfilling. Often, you will realize you gain more in return (perhaps in other ways) by giving without expectations. Alternatively, let’s start by staying kind. ❤️ Sunday was a bright sunny day, and I think it will be perfect day to view Mt Fuji. I miss my time in Japan especially the short stint in Tokyo 3 years ago. I wonder how have my classmates been? A short period of fate brought us together from different parts of the world. Always grateful for that break and the biggest takeaway: 天下没有不散之筵席. I’ll think of them at times and hope everyone is doing fine! So on Sunday, I did what I’m best at: Shopping for hours in my Mt Fuji mask- from Northpoint city to Causeway point. ❤️

text:
🥊KEEP PUSHING 🥊

As we move forward in our 8 week challenge, we should slowly start to see the changes happening. Your body may also be getting tired as your motivation has allowed you to train hard and often. Make sure to spend time on looking after your recovery. Quality sleep is essential, but so is hydration and making sure your body is limber and flexible to handle the stresses of your workouts. 

Make sure you chat to our coaches to know more about this 💪🏽

All desserts are freshly baked and prepared upon order. 
.

text:
HEALTH IS REAL WEALTH
.
SIAPA SETUJU?
.
Sudah tiba masanya untuk kita jaga kesihatan kita dengan sebaik-baik nya
.
Siapa setuju kita dah bertahun-tahun  abaikan kesihatan tubuh badan kita?
.
Yg dah mula rasa sakit2 di kaki, sesak2 nafas, rasa semput... ini menandakan kekuatan dalaman kita dah mula berkurangan...
.
Ini ada lah early warning supaya kita mula jaga kesihatan kan?
.
WE ARE WHAT WE EAT
.
Jangan kita berkira untuk berikan yang terbaik buat badan kita.
Invest in our health.
You will not regret it when u see the happiness and joy of your loved ones around you when they see you in the pink of health
.
JOM! Kita mula jaga pemakanan dgn berdiet berjemaah dlm group-coaching
.

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 29, 2020.
text:
•RECIPE•  If you have tried 莆田 lor mee, this is similar to that! I got some clams recently and decided to make this because it adds so much flavour to the broth. The broth tastes amazing with so much seafood in a pot. Plus, not much seasoning is needed.

I always thought you need a specific type of noodles but I used the egg noodles from @wulihaonoodles and it goes really well. Pair it with some sambal belachan 💯💯. I am going to make this for my family and in laws and I am sure it will be a hit! ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
• @wulihaonoodles egg noodles
• Clams
• Pork Lard (optional) 
• 6 prawns
• A few stalk xiao bai cai
• Half onion, sliced
• tau pok, cut into small pieces
• A few shittake mushroom, sliced
• 500ml chicken broth
• 1 tbsp sesame oil
• 1 tsp soy sauce

METHOD:
1) Pan fry garlic and onion and prawn head till fragrant
2) Add in taupok and mushroom and fry. Add the chicken broth. 
3) Add in condiments and simmer for 5 mins. 
4) Add in clams and vegetable and simmer for 30 seconds. 
5) Add in the noodles and simmer till noodle is cooked. 
6) Drizzle some Chinese wine and serve hot. ============================================================ #oldschool #putien #clans #noodles #15minutemeals #instadinner #instafood #15minutesrecipe #simple #sgig #sgrecipes #sgfoodie #sgfoodies #sgfoodstep #instagfoodsg #singaporehomecooks #homecookedmeals #whati8today #instagfoodsg #家常便饭 #sgfoodlover #onepotmeal #comfortfoods #circuitbreakersg

image_desc: Photo by Menus & Venues 🇸🇬 on August 29, 2020.
text:
One of our go-tos in #orchard Rd is this Malay-Indonesian restaurant at the top of @tangssg, @dancingfish.sg. Each time we go there, we try something new.

Funnily enough, though they are famous for their crispy "dancing fish", we usually prefer to order meats. Last night we tried their barbeque duck with percik sauce (really excellent) and their oxtail (extremely tender though I found the style a tad too sweet). I love their egg dishes so we had their flossy prawn #omelette. For veg we had #sambal kailan with prawn, which had a great spicy kick. We supplemented these with yellow rice (not shown).

image_desc: Photo by @sgplantstories on August 29, 2020.
text:
Breynia disticha 'Roseo-picta'
I've always thought it was a small compact shrub till I saw it looking quite different after #circuitbreakersg . It became tall (about 1.2m here), with larger leaves and a more porous body. It became clear that it's distinctive white and pink new leaves (probably where its variety name comes from) were a result of regular pruning.

This plant is a caterpillar host plant (see the chewed up leaves in pic 2), and has little green flowers hidden among the stems (which passersby will never see 😅)

#sgplantstories #plantsofsg #breyniadisticharoseopicta

text:
先週から又痛風で歩けない旦那氏…やっと治りました〜😵 これからは彼に毎日1-2Lの水分補給と食品のプリン体含有量に気をつけ無いと…本当に大変でしたわ😓 近くのNTUCスーパーで珍しく讃岐うどんが売ってました！韓国産ですが、味とツルツルの食感は讃岐うどんです❣️S$7.95 で2パックはなんとお徳👍.
.
歩けるようになった旦那氏で、夕方は一緒に近くのPark Connecorで散歩しました〜.
.
皆さん良い週末をお過ごしください❣️Stay Safe & Healthy Always 💪🏻.
.
上周脚痛风復犮导致无法走动的老爷...唉～终于好了...😓 除了毎日要叮嘱老爷多喝水(1-2L) 也要多注意飲食方面了！.
.
平日要买讃岐うどん (Sanuki Udon) 需要去Donki 
沒想到NTUC 也有卖Sanuki Udon了😲
目前有优惠 $7.95 for 2 packs 虽说是Made in Korea 
其QQ和滑溜溜的口感 Sanuki Udon 无误👍
喜欢Sanuki Udon的朋友 別錯过！
.
痛风多天的老爷 说脚好了 要出门散步去
傍晚时分 雨停了 到附近的Park connectors 走走
久沒来 树木都長高了 新建的HDB也快要完成了
一眨眼 后天就是9月了…… 真希望疫情可以早日解决 
.
㊗️大家 周末愉快 平安健康 Stay Safe 💪🏻.
.

text:
There are a variety of factors that can impact our mental health. It’s important that we each recognize and implement some simple lifestyle changes that can help us experience and enjoy better mental health.

1) Sleep
2) Physical Activity
3) Good Nutrition
4) Managing Stress
5) Do something you enjoy
6) Care for others

Mental well-being is something very personal and varies greatly from person to person. Let’s try to be sensitive to those around us and reach out with ideas on how to cope with the changes in their life.
.
.
.
.

🔥GOOD NEWS! ❤️❤️🕊️ Indonesia mulai pembicaraan awal tentang "travel corridor" bareng Singapore! Woah, ada apa yah?
.
🌟Dilansir dari The Jakarta Post, Indonesia dan Singapore akan membicarakan tentang pembukaan border travel corridor antar dua negara ini. Menteri Luar Negeri, Retno Marsudi juga datang ke Singapore untuk bilateral meeting pada hari Senin😊
.
👀Dalam meeting tersebut, mereka membicarakan tentang Preparation Indonesia-Singapore Annual Leaders Retreat dan rencana "Travel Corridor Arrangement" untuk keperluan bisnis. Sebelumnya, Indonesia juga sudah meminta Singapore untuk membuka border antar negara melalui Bintan dan Batam😉
.
👉🏻Menteri Luar Negeri menyatakan: "The two (sides) agreed that the issues that could be discussed at the leaders' retreat, included strengthening cooperation in the fields of  health, economy, and finance".
.
🌟Nah follow up dari Bilateral meeting tersebut akan disusun beberapa working grup untuk membahas beberapa issue: investment, human resource, transportation, agricultur, tourism, dan juga Bintan-Batam-Karimun (BKK) cooperation.
.
👀Such a good news kan?? tag teman mu dan kasih tahu berita baik ini!😉 yuk indo semangat buat turunin rates covid! semangatt💪🏻🙏🏻
.

Foodspot: 49 SEATS

Food looked so good that I forgot to take a proper pic. I got their weekday lunch deal which was $14.90 net for a main+ soup with garlic bread + drink. Mine was the Fish & chips with Tom yam sauce (recommend the add on request of 49 spice level for ppl who can take spicy food!!), with mash potatoes and garden salad. Can I just say that their serving is sooo humongous??? Their fish is almost twice the size of my huge palm and they gave 2 scoops of mash potatoes. The highlight is their tomyam 49 spicy sauce, super shiok for a spice lover like me. Highly recommend this place which has great service too.

Foodspo rating: 4.9/5.0

Thanks @foodspo.koh for the recommendations 💫

image_desc: Photo by 🍀🌻🌸Juewee🌸🌻🍀 on August 27, 2020.
text:
🍀Normal day, let me be aware of the treasure you are. Let me learn from you, love you, bless you before you depart. Let me not pass you by in quest of some rare and perfect tomorrow. Let me hold you while I may, for it may not always be so. 🍀 Normal days are rare. Treasure even the most normal day as it usually holds something special - which you will realize only when it’s gone. During this CB, sleeping well or through the night become rare for me. So if I were to sum up the week, it’s the first in a long time that my sleep quality has improved. Maybe it’s the newly invested silk pillowcase, maybe it’s the pillow mist, maybe it’s the new pyjamas . 😅 In any case, I don’t want to jinx it so I continue to use present tense...sleep well. Sleep is so important- even more important than exercising. When you have good sleep, you have more energy to focus and work well. Your mood improves, everything also 看得顺眼。😆So if you are blessed to sleep easily and well, please treasure it! 🤣 It’s again the last working day of the week! TGIF everyone and enjoy the weekend! 🥳🥳🥳 Btw, a friend commented my coffee stencil art today looks like a goldfish! What do you think? 🤣

image_desc: Photo shared by 🍀🌻🌸Juewee🌸🌻🍀 on August 27, 2020 tagging @crafty_mama_house. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
🎼There is a wonderful, mystical law of nature that the three things we crave most in life- happiness, freedom, and peace of mind - are always attained by giving them to someone else. 🎼 Sometimes, the more you give to others, the more you will receive in return. So do be generous with giving, caring and sharing. ❤️ busy day yesterday as I went out for lunch and to buy some cake ingredients. Wanted to replicate the chocolate fudge cake for my family to try. Tried a new dining place and I’m quite puzzled by this Ham/boiled egg creation. It’s creative, interesting but just doesn’t taste nice. It’s hard and bland, and doesn’t go well with the croissant. Sometimes, maybe it’s good enough to just stick to the basics- gently grilled or just original cold ham + diced hard boiled eggs with mayonnaise in a croissant. 🤣Other than the disappointed lunch, my day was still fine! 💐 Wore spring-looking nice floral mask, bought new flowers and baked a chocolate fudge cake again! This time, I made an effort to make it more decent looking. I hope it taste good too! Looking forward to eating it tonight! ❤️

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in The Pinnacle@Duxton with @sandviich.
text:
👉🏻Nyari "Eye-Bird" view di Singapore yang hemat di kantong? 🥰
.
🌟Kamu harus pindah haluan ke The Pinnacle @ Duxton! Di ketinggian 50 lantai, bangunan ini menawarkan pemandangan yang mengesankan! The Pinnacle @ Duxton sebenarnya adalah perumahan publik tertinggi di Singapore, disana juga ada Skybridge khusus penghuni condo. Dek observasi yang untuk umum buka pukul 09: 00-21:00 setiap hari. Yang mengejutkan, dek observasi ini tidak mengenakan harga yang fantastis! 💰💰
.
❤️Pemandangan 360 derajat dari puncak The Pinnacle nggak kalah bagus. Kalau menatap ke bawah ada atap-atap oranye di Chinatown dan view ke CBD yang menjulang tinggi. Deck ini memiliki taman dengan sejumlah sunloungers yang tersebar dan hanya menerima 200 orang umum untuk masuk setiap harinya😁
.
📍How to get there: Kamu bisa ke Blk 1G, Level 1 dan cari Kantor MA. Staf akan mendaftarkan kartu dan meminta pembayaran. Pembayaran dilakukan melalui cash dan dihargai SGD 6 per entri. Setelah pembayaran, ambil lift di Blk 1G ke lantai 50, dan lanjutkan menuju pintu masuk pintu masuk. Bisa juga kok pakai EZ-Link!
.
🚇Nearest MRT: Tanjong Pagar, ambil exit kearah Cantoment Road.
.
🌟Ada yang pernah ke hidden gem ini?😉 Tag teman kamu yang belum tahu!
.
📸Photo by: @sandviich 
.

#HaveFunWithSGB

text:
Sometimes, people sign up for classes not fully understanding what they signed up for. Sometimes they expect to be hiking and pushing up some trails, sometimes they expect to be bent into a certain pose. Sometimes they expect adrenaline to be coursing through their veins...Happy to say that, always, always...while we cannot meet their expectations, we go beyond and wow them with an unforgettable experience that is felt in their bodies, minds and spirits.⁠
⁠
Sometimes (no, often times!), we've worked hard enough. We need to go soft on ourselves too. Work hard-work soft; work out-work in.⁠

text:
🍀If you feel no enthusiasm or inspiration in a particular day, try to remember a joyful experience from your past. The joy you got from your previous achievements will carry you through. 🍀 oh I experience mental block very often, be it baking, foodart, chocolate painting or Japan travel blogging. Currently I think the mind block still exist for my blogging, which hopefully will achieve a breakthrough soon. ❤️ Anyway, today I decided to create my economical fried beehoon with a lady. This time, I purposely painted different facial features- long narrow single eye-lid eyes, rounder nose, straight eyebrowns and round face. More oriental looking but still pretty! I need to practice on drawing facial features. 💪💪💪 After lunch, I had nice chocolate fudge cake which I baked last night. 🤩 Happy midweek everyone! 🤗🤗🤗

image_desc: Photo shared by Venetia Ngin on August 25, 2020 tagging @coach_jm.
text:
As meimei's childcare started staggering arrival timings for different levels at the start of phase 2 #circuitbreaker, her N1 level got allocated the earliest 7-730am slot.
Mama used to send her in around 9am.
.
Luckily jiejie's primary school also started staggering timings & her P2 level got the 740am arrival timing (from 720am previously).
This meant that papa had to transform into a race car driver, sending meimei in first, followed by jiejie.
.
Those who have kids in childcare know that, sometimes we have to Q to enter, especially with the stringent checks now, the waiting time is prolonged.
There were a few times whereby jiejie's school teacher messaged me to check why she was not in school yet even at 740am. 🤦‍♀️
.
But what to do, because meimei's school is near one of the foreign workers' dormitories & we take the same LRT line as the workers when I send and fetch her, I think it's best that papa still remains a race car driver, for now la.
Most importantly meimei has gotten used to the early mornings so mama can 放心 abit.
.
.
.
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by Sheryl -Food & Travel Blogger🌎 in Singapore with @sherbakes.
text:
🍜What’s your favourite cuisine?! It’s Japanese for me! Miso Ramen + Crispy Japanese croquettes make the best meal! 🍜 Check our my DIY ramen at home👇🏼⁣
⁣
Ingredients for Ramen Broth:⁣⁣
❤️2-3 cups prawn/pork broth ( I cooked prawn shells/head, garlic and pork bones in a slow cooker for 8-10 hours) and then strained to get the broth⁣⁣
❤️1 tbsp minced garlic ⁣⁣
❤️1 yellow onion, chopped into fine pieces⁣⁣
❤️2 tbsp shallots oil ⁣⁣
❤️5 pieces shiitake mushrooms, soaked to soften⁣⁣
❤️ 7-8 pieces of dried scallops⁣⁣
❤️1/4 cup milk ⁣⁣
❤️Red chilli flakes (optional)⁣⁣
❤️3 tbsp white/ red Miso paste⁣⁣
❤️2 tbsp chopped chives ⁣⁣
❤️1 tbsp cornflour with 2 tbsp water⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Steps:⁣⁣
1)In a pot, add 2 tbsp shallot oil and fry garlic and onion until fragrant and garlic slightly brown⁣⁣
2)Add prawn/pork broth, dried scallops, mushrooms and let simmer 2-3 mins until onions are soft ⁣⁣
3)Add in milk, miso paste and red chilli flakes and let simmer another 2-3 mins. ⁣⁣
4)Mix cornflour with water and add it to the broth if you want a thicker broth (if not omit this step)⁣⁣
5)Throw in spring onions and stir for 1 min⁣⁣
6)Pour on TOP of cooked Ramen! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Probably missing some Japanese essential ingredients but it will do for a quick Ramen fix ❤️ Let me know if you have a recipe that rocks ok! 😘⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣

image_desc: Photo by Mix In Grace | Grace on August 25, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'Come Away Beloved'.
text:
Eggless Fluffy Green Tea Chia Pancakes😋 The pancakes were fluffy and thick. Chia Seeds gave the crunchy bites.🌰 Topped them with Strawberries🍓, Banana slices🍌, Blueberries and Cashew nuts. .
.
✳Recipe✳
Dry Ingredients:
Flour - 60g
Rolled Oats - 2 tbsp 
Baking Powder - 1tsp

Wet Ingredients:
Chia Egg - 1 qty
(1 tsp of Chia Seeds with 3 tsp of water. Let it sit in the fridge for 10 minutes.)
Green Tea/ Milk - 110ml
Coconut Oil - 1 tbsp

Cooking:
Coconut Oil - 1 tbsp

1. Combine Dry Ingredients well.
2. Add in all Wet Ingredients and mix well. Don't over mix.
3. Heat up the pan in medium low heat with the coconut oil.
4. Scooped up one heaping tablespoon of batter and place the batter onto the pan. Spread it into a circular pattern or any shape desired. Let your creativity juices run! :D
5. Flip pancakes.
6. Serve the Pancakes with Pure Honey/ Chocolate and Fresh Fruits.
.

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Singapore with @surrealhk. May be an image of 3 people.
text:
👻 Hungry Ghost Festival sebentar lagi!!!😉
.
👉🏻Apatuh min???! Kok namanya serem banget!😨😨
.
🌟Puncak Hungry Ghost Festival tahun ini jatuh pada tanggal 2 September 2020.  Nah di periode bulan hantu ini, orang Tionghoa meyakini, pintu neraka sedang dibuka dan roh-roh akan berkeliaran dan mengunjungi keluarga mereka👻
.
👉🏻Orang-orang Tionghoa akan membakar dupa dan uang kertas, memberi makanan dan juga doa untuk menenangkan roh-roh tersebut. Di jalan juga biasanya ada penampilan seperti tarian, nyanyian atau chinese opera untuk menghibur roh-roh. Tapi ditahun ini, semuanya berubah agak sepi, misalnya Getai Show yang menjadi online dan kuil kuil hanya melayani sedikit orang untuk memenuhi aturan jarak yang aman.
.
🌟Festival ini biasanya diadakan di kawasan Chinatown. Biasanya sih kamu bisa lihat berbagai sajian makanan atau dupa di sudut sudut jalan. Ada yang pernah ke SG pas periode hungry ghost festival? Share dong pengalamanmu~
.

.

text:
🌻We have no right to happiness. It is an astounding gift. 🌻Happiness is a gift from God: it’s up to us to discover the kind of happiness that works for us. Guess I will be eating bread very often these few days. So today I chanced upon two cute ig images of a poodle and Miffy. I tried to recreate them on my bread, using peanut butter and Nutella. (No white bread, so it has to be a Nutella Miffy). I even tried to create some fur-like texture with my bamboo skewer. I think the final product looks quite cute! 🥰 This is a filling brunch consisting of 3-4 slices of bread, 1 hard boiled egg and a cup of tea and it’s making me sleepy. I’m glad I have aircon, flowers and cafe style jazz music to get through the afternoon. 🎼🎷🎹 Feeling calm and therapeutic while wfh. ❤️😌😌😌

image_desc: Photo by Pam & Ping | Singapore Foodie in Hock Prawn Mee.
text:
Hungry at night? We decided to try these prawn noodles since its in the central and hurray - its 24hrs!

We tried the prawn soup and the dry prawn noodles with intestines and came to the conclusion that this place is only popular because it’s open late. Also, the dry noodles seem to be preferred as the chilli is the store’s highlight. Still, it’s not something that we would purposely make a trip down for again.

For a 24hr establishment we expected them to be well stocked with ingredients, but to our dismay, there were no beansprouts or kangkong left for our noodles. Boy, were we glad though that we had arrived earlier because the group that ordered after us did not have pork slices for their noodles - rationing is  probably why their ingredients are not so generous. Soup-wise is slightly better than average where you can taste the prawn essence after hours of boiling - with no fishy taste.

There is a sign indicating that customers could have a 1 time soup top-up, which is great to warm up your stomach at night. When we saw it, we were pleased, but when we asked for the soup top up, we were also given an extra ingredient - an additional eye roll.

Other than that, this place is nothing to rave about - just a late night eatery

Our rating: 2/5

image_desc: Photo by KOPI DATE on August 24, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'QUARANTINE CHECKLIST WHICH OF THE FOLLOWING HAVE YOU ACCOMPLISHED DURING LOCKDOWN? Dyed/ cut my hair and it surprisingly looked good Unconsciously became addicted to TikTok Wore the same pijamas for days Rewatched all my favorite TV series'.
text:
Boredom during lockdown has led us to do all kinds of activities to pass the time. The internet saved us by giving us Tiktok, Netflix, Youtube and other streaming platforms to pass the time. Some of us got a little more creative and were inspired by the countless haircutting videos to try and become an impromptu hairdresser. Which of the above have you done while you were stuck at home? Tag a friend and comment below the activities you completed!

On a more serious note, after months of circuit breaker, it is normal to lose our connection to the environment beyond our houses. We may have started feeling socially inept due to the constant isolation. Texting your ex might then come as a safe choice, either out of boredom or vulnerability, or because meeting someone new in the current situation just seems unlikely. 

Kopi Date offers a safe space for genuine connections to form and develop. We invite you to sign-up for a date with us, reconnect with the outside world, and challenge you to a unique experience.

We’re modern, 21st century, independent women. We can afford our own rings. 💍💁🏻

image_desc: Photo by De Kinder Club on August 24, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'Earth Dcrust Crust Mantle 3 Outer Core Inner Inner Core echnology IE ngineering Mathematics athematics KINDER CLUB'.
text:
“I never knew my child would be able to understand so much!”

Our S.T.E.A.M. class for preschoolers – Kinder S.T.E.A.M. is one of the very few classes in Singapore that offers a true S.T.E.A.M. curriculum. It is a pre-primary science class, that includes all other aspects of S.T.E.A.M., like technology, engineering, art and math, all rolled into one class. 

In the same class, the children could be dabbling with an experiment involving milk (learning about breaking down of fats in milk), then constructing a robotic arm, using q-tips to create a skeleton art piece, then learning about even and odd numbers in relation to body parts! The general knowledge gained, learning to ask questions, think creatively and problem solve, is what would be highly beneficial in a child’s learning journey. 

Benefits of S.T.E.A.M. in early childhood:
- Develop critical thinking 
- Develop problem-solving skills

Staying fit : A little everyday is better than none.

text:
How Many Of You Go To Hair Salon To Destress and Recharge? 🙋🏻‍♀️

A lot of people always commented that I am blessed with thick and long hair. You might not know that I have sensitive scalp and poor health conditions which lead to frizzy hair, hair loss and lots of grey/ white hair. For me, I would say that I am truly blessed with good people and services around me. 

Thanks to @junmingjoonmin and team of @crescendohairdressing 
for taking great care of my #haircut / #haircolouring / #hairtreatment / #hairrebonding and #scalptreatment for coming to 3 years. Using the premium #hairproducts and giving me good advices on #haircare. 

Mucota Treatment is excellent and it does not contain any harmful chemicals like formaldehyde.

Naturally Soft, Smooth & Silky Hair 
* Nano Size Technology 
* Natural Moisturing Factor 
* Cell Membrane Complex 
* Long-Lasting Treatment (up to 8 weeks) 
* Ultimate Shine & Softness

I am indulged with the organic hair treatment products and during #circuitbreakerperiod , Jun Ming advised me what kind of hair colouring treatment which I could get from Watson or Guardian Pharmacy and WhatsApp-ed me to arrange appointment once his hair salon could attend to service me again. 

My sincere gratitude towards his kindness, friendship and attentive services. Being a business owner is not an easy journey, I could see his passions, perseverance and politeness towards customers, no hard sell, patience explanation towards some of their requests (I.e. he strongly discouraging me to bleach my hair. He would always tell me “I would like to see you having long and healthy hair instead”) 

After #circuitbreakersg , whenever I am at the hair salon, I could see how they take precaution measures by taking temperature, scan QR code, disinfectant the seating area and giving hand-sanitisers to customers. 

Hair salon is an essential personal hair care services industry and important to make customers feel welcome, relax and valued for service. The moment you step out, you will be happy to feel good and look good. Give me a 🙌🏻 if you agreed ☺️

image_desc: Photo by 49 SEATS on August 24, 2020. May be an image of 2 people.
text:
Swipe right for drool worthy photos!!! 

It’s salted egg and tomyum feast here @49seats! Really love how flavourful the dishes here ✨ .

We had the .
🐟🐣🍟Fish and Chips with Tom Yum Salted Egg Sauce .
🐣🦐🍝Tom Yum Salted Egg Pasta with Chicken Cutlet (Level 49 Spicy) .
🐣💥Salted Egg Popcorn Chicken .
🍬🥤Sour Plum Cola .

Ok so for both main dishes I ordered Tom Yum and Salted Egg sauce and... no regret at all ✨✨✨ This sauce really is something else guys.. the creamy, aromatic sweet and tantalising salted egg sauce joined forces with the bold yet fresh and slightly tangy and spicy tom yum. Soooo good!! If you haven’t try this combo, please try it soon. They really complement each other harmoniously ☀️✨ .

The fish and chips is soo big tho! 🐟🐣🍟 Its deep fried perfectly making it has this crispy golden brown colour exterior! The fish itself is breaded with breadcrumbs and still so tender, juicy and tasted fresh 😋 its served in a bed of straight cut fries and generous amount of tom yum salted egg sauce with prawns and mussel .

For the pasta 🐣🦐🍝 we just gotta go with level 49 spicy 🌶🌶 Happy that i could still endure the heat, tho admittedly i drank after my 2nd bite 🌶🧊 Aside from adding more spicyness to the sauce I noticed there are more chilli padi too in here! This dish really wakes me up and served with huuge chicken cutlet, mussel, prawns and lala! .

Popcorn chicken also has a generous amount of sauce which i loved! 🐣💥 i like that the size of it just nice ✨ not to big that it will distract the experience, but also not to small that you could only taste the batter ✨ .

Aand i found my new fave drink too, sour plum cola! 🍬🥤its fizzy, sweet sour and slightly salty. Definitely it will quenches your thirst after a delectable meal here ✨ .

Thank you @foodirectory.sg for making all of us hungry !

image_desc: Photo by Menus & Venues 🇸🇬 on August 23, 2020.
text:
We had #kagoshima ramen from #menyasanji Tanjong Pagar last night. We had actually intended to go to #hakataikkousha across the street, but there was a bit of a wait and we were too hungry / impatient. 

So we decided to go to the empty ramen restaurant nearby –  a warning sign I guess? Maybe I ordered the wrong dish, but I must say I was a bit disappointed. Hub's #tonkotsu broth was decently rich but my #blacksesame ramen (2nd pic) was really quite bland. The soup wasn't even very hot, and the pork, while generous, was tough and chewy. Noodles and ramen egg was decent. 

Their saving grace was the gyoza, which was tasty and juicy 🥟🥟🥟. Anyway, now I still want to go to the other ramen place, which we haven't been to since #circuitbreakersg. Oh well, maybe next week!

#ramensingapore #ramenlovers #sgfoodies #sgeats #japanesefoodsg #onemealaday #foodstagram

Faham konsep present moment, kita hanya ada saat ni (NOW). Satu saat kedepan pun belum tentu lagi kita masih ada untuk selesaikan perkara yang kita letak "nanti-nanti" tu.
.
Bila fikirkan DIRI SENDIRI, kita patut dah rasa motivated dah untuk buat sesuatu tu. If dah rasa tak best berat lebih, dah tak selesa badan sendiri, dah makin tak sihat, cuba duduk depan cermin tanya diri sendiri "Adakah ini yg you deserve? Adakah ini your goals?"
.
If jawapannya tak, do something! Kita hanya dapat result hasil usaha kita bila kita put effort buat sesuatu yg membantu kita achieve goals kita
.
InsyaAllah you'll do ur best utk diri you sendiri bukan just go with the flow. Usually, yang go with the flow ni hanyalah ikan yg dah mati tak boleh nak berenang dah 🤷🏻‍♀
.
Everyday is a new day. New opportunity. Bersyukur & buat yang terbaik💪🏼
.
Good night 🤍

PHASE 2 DAY 65 -

One activity that we are thankful that reopened was SWIM.

JO LOVES THE POOL.
I remember him bugging me everyday during #circuitbreakersg when he can go back to swim. When phase 2 happened and then swimming was OK to resume, we jump back in almost immediately.

I think it's not so much about 100% safe anymore... But how do we carry on with life and adapt with the COVID-19 situation. We are constantly observing and never complacent about our decisions. We just have to weigh everything and make the best call we can ever make.

I'm glad that even before COVID-19 happen, AquaBambinos have already been very cautious about hygiene, sanitation, temperatures and even class size.
This period is not easy and we surely hope we can all ride through this and emerge stronger than before. 💕

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Gardens by the Bay with @_jessbotha_.
text:
👉🏻Asik, udah ada sinyal nih buat traveler ke Singapore! 🌈😜
.
🌟Pertanda baik nih buat traveler! Mulai tanggal 1 September, general traveler dari Brunei dan New Zealand bisa masuk ke Singapore tanpa STAY-HOME-NOTICE! Tapi mereka harus di tes covid-19 pada saat kedatangan. Durasi SHN (Stay home notice) juga dikurangi dari 14 hari menjadi 7 hari untuk beberapa negara, seperti Australia (excluding Victoria State), Macau, China, Taiwan, Vietnam, dan Malaysia. Traveler dari negara-negara tersebut juga harus tes covid-19 sebelum masa SHN-nya di Singapore berakhir😊
.
🌟Pengunjung dari Brunei dan New Zealand perlu mengajukan Air Travel Pass (surat permohonan yang akan dimulai pada 1 September nanti) antara tujuh dan 30 hari sebelum tanggal kedatangan. Mereka juga harus bertanggung jawab atas tagihan medis jika mereka memerlukan perawatan medis untuk Covid-19 saat traveling di Singapura💛
.
👉🏻Gimana, such a good news kan? Menurut kalian kira-kira.. Indonesia kapan ya? Ditunggu kabar baiknya!😍🥰
.
📸Photo by: @_jessbotha_ 🌹🕊
📲Source: Straits Times
.

It's been a while since I had time to post on Instagram, but here's the second project we (@syncroony ) had embarked on during CB period. 😝 #throwback
.
I'm super grateful for the chance to play an even bigger role in this, as one of the female leads and, once again, editing the videos together to produce this heart-warming piece. It's a tribute to the frontline and 'essential' workers, covering the song "Lean on Me" by Bill Withers, emphasising our gratitude towards those who work hard to help keep society going during this tough period.
.
Am also super tickled that the video has garnered 1000 views on Youtube and is also part of NLB's growing COVID-19 archives. 🥰 I'm glad that the message has reached so many and I hope that it has brightened our audience's day! ❣
.
.
So here's me hoping to brighten yours too by sharing this here! 😍🥰
.
👆Tap on the link in my bio for full vid (and my finale solo parts hehe)! 💕
.

image_desc: Photo by Suzie Koh-Caroline on August 22, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'HOKEIZUS'.
text:
A sweet pink, deep blue and crystal white colour combination necklace doubling up as a mask chain, this piece took much effort and time in the making. 

The focal necklace piece is made of 3 pink polygonal Morganites (17-18mm) with carved clear quartz in between, followed by iridescent deep blue Swarovski pearl, rose quartz and another iridescent white Swarovski pearl  interlaced with faceted glass rondelles.

The rest of the chain is made up of faceted 5mm moonstone, lapis Lazuli and rhodochrosite, painstakingly double-looped and linked all the way to the 2 lobster clasps.

The interesting thing about this piece is that the focal necklace piece can be removed and easily replaced with another design later on , similar concept to Pandora charms. However, you will have to get Hokeizus to customise another design it for you!

We are pledging 20% to @HPHPcommunity and @Mettacats_and_Dogs_sanctuary,  for every piece sold, DM for details.

text:
•RECIPE•  Too tired to cook for dinner after a long meeting. Made an old school dish and a soup and we have a comforting dinner in less than 30 minutes! 
===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
• 2 potatoes, sliced or cubed
• 150g minced meat (seasoned with 1tsp cornflour, 1 tsp sesame oil, 1tsp soy sauce) 
• 1 tbsp oyster sauce
• 1 tsp dark spy sauce
• 1 stalk spring onion
• A dash of pepper 

METHOD:
1) Pan fry some potato till both sides are slightly browned 
2) In the same pan, add in some garlic and fry till fragrant. Add in the minced meat and mix well. Add in the condiments
3) Add in the potatoes and mix well. 
4) Add some water and simmer for 2 minutes or till potatoes softens. 
5) Add in the spring onion before serving and mix well.
6) Serve hot. ============================================================ #oldschool #mincedpork  #pork #15minutemeals #15minutesrecipe #simple #sgig #sgrecipes #sgfoodie #sgfoodies #sgfoodstep #instagfoodsg #singaporehomecooks #homecookedmeals #whati8today #instagfoodsg #家常便饭 #sgfoodlover #onepotmeal #comfortfoods #circuitbreakersg

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 22, 2020 tagging @nowbakerysg.
text:
Look at these lovely sweet treats from @nowbakerysg ! From their signature blancmange roles to hokkaido vanilla cream cupcakes and double flavor classic chocolate and almond coffee cake, each of them had very soft and moist sponge and flavorful fillings.

I especially loved their signature coffee gula melaka rolls ($14.90) because of the thick, rich blancmange filling, which is like milk pudding. The intense aroma of coffee and gula melaka was very pleasant, and the aftertaste of this roll was much lighter than other cakes.

The hokkaido cupcakes ($15.90) were another attention grabber due to its fluffy outer puffs loaded with creamy vanilla fillings. These puffs really reminded of the moist cakes I had in Japan due to its high quality fresh vanilla cream.

The classic cakes ($17.40) came in two flavors, chocolate and almond coffee and these were much for dense and heavy compared to the swiss roll. Chocolate cake was very fudgy and thich, which went very well milk and the coffee cake’s faint scent of almond was especially pleasant.

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Buddha Tooth Relic Temple and Museum with @erick.tan.
text:
🤔Apa sih isinya Buddha Tooth Relic Temple Singapore? 
.
👉🏻Banyak area di dalamnya yang bisa kamu lihat! 😁☺️✨Misanya, 100 Dragon Hall —ruangan utama yang terdapat patung Buddha Maitreya setinggi 15 kaki yang dikelilingi oleh 100 patung Buddha dan 100 patung Naga! Wow!🔥
.
🌟Avalokitesvara Hall, area dimana patung buatan Bodhisattva Cintamanicakra Avalokitesvara yang sedang duduk diatas bunga lotus dan bersamaan dengan patung zodiac protector. Ada juga Buddhist Culture Museum yang berisikan artefak-artefak Buddha😁
.
🌟Di lantai tiga, kamu bisa beristirahat sejenak dan menikmati secangkir teh di sebuah kedai. Ada makanan vegetarian juga lho. Sedangkan, Relic Gigi Buddha sendiri berada di lantai empat✨
.
Sebelum mampir, pahami dulu biar lebih leuasa explore kuil & museum ini nantinya! Ditunggu yah di SG setelah pandemic mereda😉😉
.
💰FREE
🚇 Nearest MRT: Chinatown (exit pagoda street)
📍288 S Bridge Road
.

Oh I’m wearing my new Mt Fuji inspired mask today! I miss Japan travelling! Every. Single. Day. ❤️ Happy Saturday! 🤩

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 21, 2020 tagging @gimpohfood.
text:
Kong Bak Pau conveniently made thanks to @gimpohfoodsg ! 

These amazing “cooked” braised pork belly arrive frozen at your door step so all you need to do is just heat them up before you eat! I briefly simmered mine for 10 mins and it was as good as freshly cooked kong bak pao. 

For the buns, I steamed them using the rice cooker for 8 mins and it came out to be soft and hot, just nice for my pork belly. Adding cheese on my braised pork belly buns was extremely delicious as well.

The handmade prawn balls also came in frozen state that were already deep fried, so just toss them on your air fryer for 10 mins and they become very crispy outside and moist inside! They went very well with chilli and mayonnaise as well🙆🏻‍♀️

image_desc: Photo by Menus & Venues 🇸🇬 on August 21, 2020.
text:
We had a wonderful Italian dinner with a friend at @osoristorante last night, on top of #oasiahoteldowntown.

We shared a bunch of appetizers including their giant #burrata, tuna #crudo and #tegamino (fried egg with truffles) 🍳. Then, we had a veal #ravioli (with cheese fondue) and the highlight of the night, a large #ribeyesteak. Honestly by then I was quite full!

For drinks, we started with cocktails and moved on to a #nebbiolo, one of my fav wine grapes 🍷🍇. 

Food and service were excellent and it was great to see the restaurant bustling with life. We had ordered takeaway from them during the #circuitbreakersg as well, but of course it's not the same.

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 21, 2020 tagging @mypiesp.
text:
Amazing pork and beef pies from @mypiesp 

This rich, hearty shepherd's pie had very generous fillings made up of seasoned minced meat and assorted diced veggies, that was topped with perfectly baked mashed potatoes. The pie was very soft and creamy, each mouthful being flavorful and filling. This wholesome pie is made from scratch using the freshest ingredients and it was delivered hot so it tasted even better. @mypiesp specializes in three different pie flavors (pork, beef and chicken), and I just love how they don't try to save on the ingredients because the pies are literally loaded with fillings. My personal favorite was the beef pie because it went so well with the creamy mashed potatoes!

#sgfood #sgfoodie #foodie #food #foodstagram #foodphotography #sgeats #sginfluencer #sgfoodies #sgsnacks #productreview #sgpies #shepherdspie #sgpiedelivery #productreview

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 20, 2020 tagging @bakked.sg. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
Beautiful brownies from @bakked.sg 

These flavorful Blackout Brownies are absolutely chewy and fudgy. 

Although the plain ones were already nice enough due to its thick and rich chocolate-y flavor, my favorite was the Speculoos brownies! The caramelised cookie dough at the core of the brownie gave the right sweet-salty touch, bringing the flavor of this delicacy to a whole new level. 

The Black Forest had a very interesting flavor as well, due to the dark pitted cherries at the core of the brownie. 

All of the brownies were very smooth and moist, and I liked microwaving them for 10-15 seconds to have it warm, which was absolutely delicious. 

Although I usually have my brownies with milk or coffee, I tried them with one of @bakked.sg 's Colonial Tea Blend, which was a fragrant Earl Grey tea. 

The scent of chamomile and citrus was very soothing and surprisingly went well with the sweet brownies.

👉🏻Box of 6 brownies with coffee/tea pairing for $40

Thanks to @bakked.sg for sending over these amazing dessert ❤️

#sgfood #sgfoodie #foodie #food #foodstagram #foodphotography #sgeats #sginfluencer #sgfoodies #sgsnacks #productreview #sgdessert #brownies #bakkedsg #sgbrownies

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 19, 2020 tagging @chillilor.sg.
text:
These crispy chillis from Thailand are extremely addictive! 

No preservatives and MSG have been added to these roasted, all natural chillis and they come in varieties of flavor. 

I started with the original flavor and because these chillis have been deseeded to reduce the spiciness, they didn't have the overwhelming "hot" taste. 

The Mala Crispy Chillis had the nice "numb" effect after every mouth so if you are a fan of mala, this is definitely the flavor you want to try. 

My favorite was the Cheesy Cheese flavor because the cheese powder went extremely well with the spiciness of the crispy chillis. 

The bestselling Tom Yum flavor had the addictive tangy sour taste and because these are low in calories, I felt less guilty finishing half jar at one sitting!

Refer to @chillilor.sg to get these crispy chillies!🌶

#sgfood #sgfoodie #foodie #food #foodstagram #foodphotography #sgeats #sginfluencer #sgfoodies #sgsnacks #productreview #chillilor

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 18, 2020 tagging @twobakeboys. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
@twobakeboys just introduced new amazing flavor to their tea crepe cake menu and it's one of the best crepe cakes I've tasted in Singapore!

This creamy Thai Green Tea Crepe Cake (S$35 for 6") is made with Thai green tea imported directly from Thailand, leaving no artificial aftertaste in every flavorful mouth.

Each thin crepe layer is covered by thick, rich green tea cream that isn't overly sweet and the generous amount of cream in each layer makes the whole cake extremely smooth. 

Although the cake itself is already good enough, adding the green tea sauce brings the flavors of the cake to a whole new level. 

The gooey bitter-sweet green tea sauce makes the cake even more moist and delectable.

If you are a fan of crepe cakes and green tea, this amazing confectionery is definitely a must-try. They also have a Thai Milk Tea flavor which is another eye-catcher.

#sgfood #sgfoodie #foodie #food #foodstagram #foodphotography #sgeats #sginfluencer #sgfoodies #sgcafe #sgcake #sgdessert #sgunited

image_desc: Photo shared by Eunsol🌸 on August 17, 2020 tagging @ettybakes.
text:
Brownie morning! 

@ettybakes just released new brownies flavor and it has become my new addiction! 

The Half and Half ($34/box), consisting of original + hazelnutmaste flavor is an august exclusive menu. The original brownies boast the classic thick and rich chocolate flavor, crispy outside and soft and moist inside. These are absolutely fudgy and chewy which go so well with fresh milk!

The new addition to the delectable family are the hazelnutmaste brownies. The crispy hazelnut filling sandwiched between the fudgy brownies made the brownies even more flavorful and aromatic. These brownies are definitely worth the calories!

.
去年Glico和新加坡本地著名珍宝海鲜 ( Jumbo Seafood )联手推出辣椒螃蟹口味的PRETZ, 还有刚在上个月和著名海南鸡饭餐馆威南记(Wee Nam Kee)联手推出的海南鸡饭口味的PRETZ, 在NTUC超市可以购买了！连Yakun的Kaya Pandan, Kopi-O Pocky也有！價格介于$1.6-1.8, 是送給海外朋友 滿有特色的伴手禮、可惜无法去旅行呀！😭.
.

Meet Jojo! ❤🐱❤ Bit late for Black Cat Appreciation Day, but hey, is it ever too late to appreciate this beauty? 
.
Jojo is a sleek & independent older lady who knows what she wants- comfort & respect! She's a curious, calm, & quietly confident kitty who gets along with other cats. 
.
Jojo has been all checked out by the vet & is in good health. On paper, her immune system is not so good (she has FIV), but she has aced her kidney/ liver profile & physical check-up. Jojo is about 11 years old & has many years of companionship left to give. 
.

text:
I haven’t visit the dentist for more than 6 months so I need a better toothbrush to remove the plaque that’s building up. Colgate ProClinical B150 Charcoal Battery Toothbrush has up to 20,000 strokes per minute and unique multi-directional cleaning. It is slim, lightweight and comes with a 2 minute timer. After using this toothbrush, I realise that I’ve been brushing my teeth for more than 2 minutes all these years. So most of the time the toothbrush stops abruptly when I’m not even done brushing. It will be good if it comes with an indicator after 1 minute so that I can adjust my speed according before it switches off automatically. Overall this toothbrush is quite effective in keeping my teeth clean. 

I am still not comfortable visiting the dentist at this stage. What about you?

text:
🌟🌟GIVEAWAY!🌟🌟
.
Anyone here missing authentic Taiwanese food? Check out @LorBakPng’s lor bak. It may remind you of your travels in Taiwan!
.
Everything is made from scratch per batch of orders by Yvonne’s mom who hails from Taiwan. Because of the pandemic, they decided to start selling their delicious Lor Bak and have been receiving great reviews. Most Lor Bak in Taiwan is 90% fats, however they’ve tried to pick meat that is a little leaner but still has enough fats to give you that melt in your mouth feel. I personally like the meat to fat ratio as it provides a good bite. 

They also sell a Spicy Minced Pork dish, another signature dish. Its very very spicy and fragrant because of the fermented black beans. In fact it’s so super spicy a little goes a long way! Painfully good! 😂
.
So here’s your chance to try out some Lor Bak. I’m going to pick three winners to win the following each:

text:
🌻I wish you friends, kind friends who care for you when you are low, who can teach you to laugh again. 🌻 Craved for some pancakes and decided to visit the newly opened pancake shop during lunch. The pancakes are delicious but the portion is too little as compared to competitor’s which offer a bigger serving for similar price. Guess it’s good only as a dessert but not aa a meal. (Then again, the pricing doesn’t justify it as a dessert.) The long waiting time also greatly compromise the overall experience. 😑In any case, the tiramisu pancakes and salted caramel pancakes are yummy! Maybe I should just cook salted caramel syrup and make my own pancake at home. Another disappointment during lunch break was not being able to find any chiffon cake pan in the mall. Haiz. Now that cake ingredients are back, the baking utensils are out of stock. 😞Other than that, the day was okay- wearing my new pretty mask, grabbing some sales during lunch shopping and having old Chang kee during teabreak. So I still managed to smile for the day. 🍀🍀🍀

image_desc: Photo shared by Vanessa Kou on August 20, 2020 tagging @farineaffair.
text:
I haven’t had that many sourdoughs in my life but @farineaffair Cheddar Rosemary ($15) is now my favourite. Adding a beautiful depth of flavour, the pockets of savoury cheddar was fragrant and intensified with the hints of rosemary. The cheddar wasn't too sharp in my opinion and provided an umami quality too. Deliciously and subtly tangy, the sourdough was surprisingly soft in the middle with a slight chew and a fabulously crunchy crust. However, great on its own, the toast tasted even more sublime with Farine Affair's compound butters!

Made with a mixture of herbs, spices, and other condiments; the Cafe de Paris Butter ($14.80 for 125g) was so aromatic. Herb-tastic, it is best served with toasted sourdough but also good with steaks. With gentle earthy notes, the Porcini Butter ($11.80 for 125g) lends a somewhat meaty flavour that is very addictive as well and goes superbly with toasted sourdough, pasta, broiled proteins, and even steamed vegetables.

Photo 3-10 : バリ島は何処でもプルメリアが咲いて、神聖な花として、毎日神様にお供えします~ プルメリアを耳に付けることは、お洒落の為だけではなく、神聖な祈りの意味合いも含まれているんです〜.
.
这几天的天氣又熱起來了、在邻里散步见到不少鸡蛋花开了落地、让我想起了巴厘岛的鸡蛋花呀⋯
.
Photo 3-10: 清香优雅的鸡蛋花在巴厘岛无所不在、家家户户供奉的神像座上、供品上都有著鸡蛋花的身影和香气～当地人也喜欢在发髻或耳边都戴着一朵鸡蛋花、除了裝饰也象徵著神明保佑的意思～.
.

text:
Can you guess what Mottainai means? 

"Mottainai is an ageless Japanese wisdom of interacting with the world such that we fully appreciate what exists, treat it as precious and make full use of its potential."

The concept of Mottainai is to harness the potential of recycled organics through scientific innovation and methods such as reducing landfill, re-using olive and carrot by-products, recycling carrot leaves, respecting our animals and reconnecting with nature. 

The spirit of @mottainai_lamb is in its sustainable food production, where food is produced to nurture and sustain. How inspiring is that!

4 days left to the launch of the extraordinary Ottoman Lamb Burger!

text:
Sabun Collagen Nurraysa ni jenis sabun yang tak banyak buih.

Kenapa macam tu? 
Sabun Collagen diperbuat dari bahan-bahan organik. Tanpa S.L.S atau S.L.E.S, sejenis agent pembuih yang boleh buat kulit kita kering dan sensitif.

Sebab itulah jika yang kerap menggunakan pencuci yang ada campuran 2 benda ini, anda akan mengalami keradangan kulit. Kulit juga akan jadi sensitif.

Fat Loss vs. Weight Loss – Yes, There is a Difference!

When trying to slim down, many people track their progress by stepping on the scale. Maybe you were happy by the low number you saw or suddenly became depressed because the number was higher than usual.

Sarah & I had been there before, so you are not alone so you don't have to be depressed about it. The number on the scale doesn’t tell you much about your health; all it tells you is your relationship with gravity.

There is a vast difference between weight loss (to which most people look at) and fat loss!

That is why in this video we are sharing with you the difference and why you should be more focused on fat loss than weight loss.

DM us for your FREE Body Composition Assessment now to understand your body better!

image_desc: Photo by The Crossing Church on August 19, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'SUNDAY SNIPPETS HOW CAN WE PRAY FOR THE CHURCH AND THE WORLD? The Crossing Church'.
text:
Most of the time our prayers are for the 5Cs - comfort, cure, career, courtship and children. God listens to every single prayer with great delight and understands the troubles of our hearts. 🥰

Philippians 4:6 tells us not to be anxious about anything, but in everything through prayer and petition, with thanksgiving, to present our requests to God. While it is good to pray for our needs, we can become more kingdom-focused like Apostle Paul.

His prayers were heavily centred around God's will and work in His world. He prayed for wisdom, to live out the gospel, to stand firm in Jesus Christ and for gospel proclamation. 🌍

As a church, may we become more kingdom-focused by continually praying more for wisdom, our walk with God, to stand firm in Christ and to proclaim the gospel. 🗣

If you’d like to learn more about Jesus, join us online on Sundays! Our Sunday Services are available from Saturdays to Mondays on thecrossing.com.sg/exploring-the-crossing/sunday-services/

To find out more about Christianity, go to thecrossing.com.sg/the-good-news/ 🎊 or link in bio!

💐The aim of life is to live, and to live means to be aware, joyously, drunkenly, serenely, divinely aware. 💐 Live fully- with awareness. 😌 Today I need to finish up the loaf of bread. Actually I prefer white bread to multi-grains one. The only way to make myself eat all these multi-grains bread is to make them as cute as possible. So I recreated them into the Hello Kitty family! 🤩🤩🤩 We have Papa George (who share the same birthday as me! 🥳), Mama Mary, Twin Sister Mimi (opps, I have to confess her ribbon should be yellow instead of pink. 🤭), Boyfriend Dear Daniel and of course, Hello Kitty herself. Together, they form the Happy Happy Family. 🥰 Seeing this really brighten up my day from the super hectic morning with influx of emails! Oh I also plate them with my limited edition Singapore Airlines Kebaya Kitty! 😍😍😍 Happy midweek!

image_desc: Photo by DabaoRight 🇸🇬 on August 18, 2020.
text:
It’s Climate Action Week by @msesingapore ! Running until 21 August, this year’s program covers topics including food sustainability, composting, urban farming, plastics and energy efficiency.

Here’s one that particularly caught our eye — a discussion with @nlb.singapore and @wwfsg on rethinking our relationship with plastic in our shopping habits and daily life. 

Eye popping facts from the event blurb… Did you know that Singapore households have generated an extra 1334 tonnes of plastic waste during the circuit breaker? That’s the weight of 92 double decker buses! 

Also, the frequency of households who bought their groceries online has jumped by 50%! Imagine how much extra packaging waste has been created… 

If you, like us, are interested about this topic, come join the webinar this coming Thursday, 20th August (7-8pm) through the link in our bio! 😉

Meanwhile, remember to BYO, folks!

image_desc: Photo shared by JOHN YEONG | SINGAPORE DIARIES on August 18, 2020 tagging @kellylatimer, @latimerbarbara, @sport_singapore, and @getactivetv. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'GETACTIVE! SINGAPORE The ionima & BARBARA Show WITH KELLY'.
text:
// 5 days. That was the only runway we had to prep all our 7 x daily shows at the start of #CircuitBreakerSG in April this year for the launch of @getactivetv as the Covid-19 pandemic hit Singapore hard. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
From ideation of each of the individual shows, to the preparation, execution and running of daily operations. From hosts, to talents, crew and staff all working together.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It was a mammoth effort to pull it off, a crazy one never done before in my life, and I have a stellar cast to thank for pulling through. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Over the course of the next few weeks, I will be mixing in throwbacks and some funny behind-the-scenes footages taken from the past 5 months into this IG journal of mine, to go with motivational posts and photos of everyday friends and people I hold dear to my heart.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Thank you for being a part of my life, and for making 2020 bearable.

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 18, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'BEEF FRIED KWA TEOW'.
text:
•RECIPE•  A comforting meal in less than 15 minutes. 
===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
• 400g kway teow
• 150g beef (seasoned with 1tsp cornflour, 1 tsp sesame oil, 1tsp soy sauce) 
• 100g bean sprout
• 3 eggs
• 1 tbsp minced garlic
• 1 tbsp fish sauce
• 1 tbsp soy sauce
• Dark sauce to colour 

METHOD:
1) Add some oil and heat beef over high heat. Remove when it's almost cooked. 
2) In the same pan, add in some garlic and fry till fragrant. Turn to high heat. Add in the kway teow and stir fry when the oil starts smoking. 
3) Add in the condiments and mix well. 
4) Push the kway teow aside and add some oil. Add in the eggs and mix well. 
5) Stir fry the eggs and kway teow together. Add in the beef and bean sprouts and fry for another 30seconds.
6) Serve hot. ============================================================ #stirfrybeef #kwayteow  #beef #30minutemeals #30minutesrecipe #simple #sgig #sgrecipes #sgfoodie #sgfoodies #sgfoodstep #instagfoodsg #singaporehomecooks #homecookedmeals #whati8today #instagfoodsg #家常便饭 #sgfoodlover #onepotmeal #comfortfoods #circuitbreakersg

text:
🥊 75 DAYS HARD CHALLENGE 🏋🏼So we have just started our #75hard challenge today. It is designed to help you prioritize and focus on your time management skills. The challenge also gets you to be disciplined and develop good structures and routines. 

I am doing this challenge as I want to always push myself to mental and physical limits. Also all my people at @boxingspartans_sg are doing the 8 Week Challenge so want to lead by example by improving as well. Message me if you are keen to join the challenge 🙏💪👍

75 HARD CHALLENGE 

Rules 

1. Must follow a diet or meal plan of your choice 
2. Drink a gallon of water a day, 3.7 litres, I recommend if you are a smaller person to adjust, like @Thuymi that will do 3L 
3. Must do 2x45min workouts a day, one of these must be outside
4. 10 minutes of reading of a non fiction book a day: I’m reading #TheArtOfWar
5. Progress Picture everyday for yourself 
6. Miss anything on any day and you must start the challenge again

.
皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe 💪🏻.

Here are 3 Smart ways to maximize your HIIT
.
📌Remember to save this post down and refer to it later!📌
.
.
⚠️HIIT workouts generally combine short bursts of intense exercise with periods of rest or lower-intensity exercise.⚠️
.
1️⃣Proper form is essential 👉 Bad form can put too much strain on the joints, work the wrong targeted muscle💪 groups and make you susceptible to injury.
.
2️⃣HIIT👉supposed to be short, intense. ⚠️To reap the benefits of HIIT you need to attack it with a lot of energy💯. You won’t reap the strength and cardio benefits from leisurely going through the movements.☝️
.
3️⃣Work to Recovery ratio👉 The duration and number of your ⚠️work and ⚠️recovery phases you perform will depend on your 💪fitness level and training goals.
.
👉For Starter/Beginner 1 to 3 ratio⚠️ 📌ie. 15 secs work phase and 45 secs recovery phase
👉Slowly progress to Immediate (1 to 1 Ratio – ⚠️📌ie 20 Secs work and 20 Secs recovery) 
👉Advance ⚠️📌(2 to 1 Ratio- ie 20 Secs work and 10 secs recovery)
.
Small breaks in between for you to work hard during work phase.
.
📌⚠️3 Smart ways to bring your HIIT to next level, ☝️REMEMBER to save it down for reference or share🔊 it with your friends who might find this useful.
.
Let's HIIT it ! W #Yvotay_fit

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Sentosa Boardwalk with @theshutterwhale.
text:
👉🏻Suka jalan kaki? Atau suka jogging? Ini 5 Alasan kenapa kamu harus coba jalan di Boardwalk Sentosa!😋🥰
.
1. Free
Dibanding transport di Sentosa lainnya, ini memang paling murah karena GRATIS! 🔥🔥🔥
.
2. Sheltered, so no fear of rain
Baik hujan maupun cerah, siang atau malam, boardwalk akan melindungi kamu dengan kanopi, (walau nggak semuanya). Dan, ini juga wheel-chair-friendly!💗💗👍🏻
.
3. Easy to access the attractions
Sentosa Boardwalk mengarah ke RWS Waterfront sehingga kamu dapat dengan mudah mengakses atraksi seperti Trick Eye Museum, S.E.A. Aquarium dan Adventure Cove Waterpark, serta restoran seperti Seafood Republic dan Malaysian Food Street!😍😁
.
4. Bisa sambil belanja & mampir makan sepanjang jalan
Kadang, setiap weekend kamu bakal melewati Sentosa Boardwalk Bazaar🛒💗
.
5. Banyak lighting pas malam
Setelah matahari terbenam, Boardwalk berubah menjadi suasana malam romantis untuk melihat bintang!🌟🌟
.
🔥Kamu pernah jalan di Boardwalk Sentosa? Apa kamu lebih milih Monorail atau Bus RWS8? Hihihi..🤪🤪
.

text:
dis-ease

A visual exploration of the pandemic ennui one encounters under lockdown. I created this series during the COVID-19 Circuit Breaker lockdown in Singapore with a pinhole lens. The method seemed fitting of the circumstances - seeing the light from the world outside filter through a tiny window into the dark confines of what is essentially a black box, rendering a bleak and muted image of the reality we now live in. image_desc: Photo shared by Samantha on August 16, 2020 tagging @wonderland_botanicals.
text:
Posted this on IG stories last week and felt it deserved a place in my feed. I know it’s just a random inanimate object... but during this solo WFH period (I’ve been going crazy from the lack of interaction!), you really start to notice the little things. Like how at 645pm everyday, the sunlight will stream through my kitchen window and beam onto this vase of flowers, reminding me its time to finish up work and start thinking about what to cook for dinner.

Today’s marks exactly 5 months of WFH life (and I was enjoying a funemployment break before that). I’ve worked from an office for a grand total of 8 days this year. How crazy is that?

image_desc: Photo shared by @thegatedreverb on August 16, 2020 tagging @gourmettraveller, @travelandleisure, @chef.drew.nocente, @8days_eat, @unlistedc, @theworlds50best, @gourmetartistry, @saltedandhung, @thebestchefsoftheworld, @michelinguide, @straitstimesfood, and @bestrestaurantsguide.
text:
@saltedandhung // Really appreciating all the catch-ups and good food (ie, not my own cooking) now that #sgrestaurants have opened (with appropriate contact-tracing, temperature-taking, social-distancing requirements).

#saltedandhung was very much better than my untrustworthy memory purports to recall - exquisitely balanced, umami bomb flavours that these words + photos fail to adequately convey:
1. 1BITE -CHEESEBURGER 
wagyu #beeftartare, beef fat smoked ketchup, pickles

2. 1BITE - uni umami panna cotta, yuzu, pickled radish, kelp oil, nori cracker

3. 1BITE - FISH & CHIPS
chickpea chip, pea purée, caviar

4. TIME, LOVE & PATIENCE
IPA #sourdough, #whippedlard with chilli oil, #wakamebutter 

5. TREASURES OF THE SEA
#rawscallops, #caviar, yuzu sake, chilli granita

6. SURF & TURF
crayfish, lemonade & charcuterie broth

7. HEART & SOUL
housemade charcuterie - duck breast, bresaola, ?

8. THE WHOLE FISH
Pearl #grouper, #bonecrumb, charcoal 
Kinda #nosetotail but with fish flesh and bones and skin. Especially cool: #fishbone roasted then infused with local soy sauce for a month. After that the bones are dried and blended to a powder. 

Will experiment with this if/when we have another #circuitbreakersg.

9. HOMELAND
#kangaroomeat, beetroot, cauliflower 
Woah, so tender and tasty. I’d look at the local roadkill a little differently next time we’re doing road trips Down Undah. Kidding.

10. MEAT, BONE & FIRE
wagyu #tritip, bone marrow, ash
That pear and shiitake reduction with bone marrow butter? Superb.
.
Right use of #modcuisine - where the medium (dehydrated things, powders (not used:gels, foam)) does not overshadow the message (properly cooked food with balanced punchy flavours).

As the birthday girl said at regular intervals throughout the meal: “everything I’ve put in my mouth has been good!”.

So much in this world that is so delicious!

image_desc: Photo by Online Wine Shop 🍷🇸🇬 Singapore in Singapore with @domainedebaronarques.
text:
A half for your better half? Love to dine out but hate bringing half empty bottles?

Or to open one for solo drinking but detest putting them back in your wine cellars? 

Try this little sweetheart from a property with some v royal flair 👑 and at a lovely price point.

Domaine de Baronarques is an old estate, dating back to the 17th Century, when it was called Domaine de Lambert. 

The estate changed several hands in the interim over the next two centuries. It got its rightful place and was transformed when in 1998 the Rothschilds of First Growth Chateau Mouton Rothschild acquired and reinvigorated the estate.

Over the next 5 years, the Rothschilds poured their heart, money and passion to return the estate to its rightful place and to its modern  day glory. 

Located in Languedoc, in the commune of Saint-Polycarpe, near Limoux, the Domaine is a single 110-hectare (272-acre) estate, 43 hectares (106 acres) of which are planted with vines.

The vineyard is subject to the climatic influence of both Atlantic and Mediterranean oceans, ensuring optimum sunshine and balanced rainfall. Also close to the Pyrenees, the parcels are at an altitude of 250 to 350 metres, tempering the summer heat.

In 2003, Domaine de Baronarques was also awarded the AOC Limoux rouge appellation, newly created by the Institut National des Appellations d’Origine (INAO). 

A blend of 48% Merlot, 22% Cabernet Franc and 7% Cabernet Sauvignon, 13% Syrah and 10% Malbec. Ageing is in 25% new and 75% 1-3yr old oak barrels.

 The wine has a lovely nose of black fruit aromas, rose, tobacco with hint of chocolate and vanilla. Offers v polished tannins and a wonderful long finish.

$42/- per btl (usual $47/-).

image_desc: Photo by 𝕃𝔼 𝕍𝕐ℝ in Singapore.
text:
How should you start drinking Kombucha for the first time? 🤩

Well the answer is simple. Our belief is to go slow. We craft our Kombucha to be palatable for everyone (kids included). 

Start with half a glass, poured over ice cubes and observe how your body feels a few hours after. (Enjoy them with tonic/sparkling water if the taste is too strong for your liking) 

If your body reacts well to it, go ahead and gradually increase your consumption! You may experience symptoms like tummy aches, flare-ups and even body aches that occurs due to toxins being encouraged to leave your body! 

If that happens, drink plenty of water and get some rest in before slowly easing back into small amounts of Kombucha after your body grows acclimated to it.

We encourage you to drink them in the morning, on an empty stomach to best experience it’s benefits. However, there is no precise time in which Kombucha must be consumed. It can be consumed in the morning as an extra morning boost during a work out, in the afternoon to combat that office lull or in the evening after dinner as an alternative to sugary desserts!

text:
IPPT has been suspended till further notice...

While many NSmen feel relieved or find that extra time has been extended to them...

The thing is... you can't put a pause on your own health and fitness.

That's why we consistently have to watch our diet and exercise daily if not regularly.

It's definitely not easy for a fact. 

I've been through what many had gone through. Getting overweight in the past while working at a 9-5, plus having to complete my degree after work got me stressed up till I reached a weight of 86kg.

Probably the heaviest my body ever gotten.

But I put in my time and focus to burn my fats off till eventually I flipped the numbers to 68kg.

At first I didn't know it was possible until I attained that goal and the rest was history.

Now, helping more and more people in their weightloss journey. 🚀

So are you still not hitting your fitness goals or always ended up failing to kickstart your weight loss goals?

Maybe you just need a personal trainer like myself.

I was once in your shoes so I know how I can help you.

But first, you have to help yourself by letting me in to help you.

And the fastest way to get started (and it's FREE), is to follow me here on IG and let me be your motivation to get you started.

You can even feel free to drop a comment or DM me.

I even have a foolproof method that's on my blog, link's on Bio. (You definitely want to check it out 👆👆👆)

... for I'm always here to help. 😉

How do we define ourselves? Like many of us, Michelle had deep questions about her identity and fundamental sense of being. 

Watch her share about how compelling the person of Jesus is to her, why she believes He is worth surrendering her entire self and identity for, and why she is assured that none of it will be in vain.

Jesus’ inclusivity and love is radically different from what society tells us. In Jesus, we see God himself in the flesh and we see God take on human suffering. In Jesus, we find that God is not asking us to do something that he hasn't already done himself.

If the person of Jesus could really provide rationally plausible explanations and emotionally satisfying answers to life’s big questions about existence, morality and injustice, why not take a serious look at the claims of Jesus? 🔍🔍🔍 #tccjesusunmasked

image_desc: Photo by Online Wine Shop 🍷🇸🇬 Singapore in Singapore with @chateau_branecantenac.
text:
The first time when we were offered a big sized parcel of Chateau Brane-Cantenac, the classified second growth property from Bordeaux, it seemed such extreme value, we rejected the offer thinking it was too good to be true. 

You can forgive us for this judgment error. You see, we were coming from a round of buying Pichon Lalande and Cos d'Estournel bottles from 1996, 2009s and 2010s. The price to value of Brane-Cantenac vis-a-vis other classified 2nd growth seemed almost ridiculously unbelievable. 

And yet that is how it has been over the last decade. 

Chateau Brane Cantenac is no longer in the shadows of some of its illustrious neighbours yet the bottles across the top vintages '05, '09, '10, '15, '16 offer the best value among second growth bottles.

The wines have always been rated v well over the last decade. So we are always on the look out for offers on these.

The Lurton family that runs the estate has owned Brane-Cantenac since 1925,. The Grand Vin comes from a single parcel of 40+ hectares.

They have also partnered with the academia for decades and extensively carry out their own research: be it wine making, or vine grafting & growing, oak ageing or modern practices in cellar management.

As Jane Anson from Decanter described it post a vertical tasting at the Chateau in 2018, "Brane is never the most showy of wines and yet it has become one of the most sought-after names in Margaux, impressing through the most beautiful layering of aromatics and textured, confident fruits, perfectly encapsulated in the 2005 and even the undervalued 2012."

2005s can be yours for $185 a bottle (normally $205). Just the last few bottles. 

DM/WA 91089395 for info or orders.

text:
⛵️Earth’s crammed with heaven.⛵️ I miss visiting beautiful flower fields in Japan. I wonder when I will be able to go back to Tokyo. Anyway it’s a rainy early morning and the Toast Box Kopivan is here again (last day for this week). I heard so much about their popular Curry Rice and decided to try it today. Omg. It’s really not bad! I would say it is better than their laksa and fried mee siam! So I think the curry rice will go to my top 3 list (the other two items are the Peanut thick toast and pork floss bun). I also recreated my curry rice set into a scene during the “National Sailing Championship 2020.” 🤣 My chicken wings and Tau Pok are recreated as sailing boats ⛵️ and I use seaweed to cut out 3 stickmen. I do think this foodart send out some relaxing vibes yah? 🤪 Hope tomorrow will also be a not-so-humid day. ⛵️⛵️⛵️ Counting down to Friday.

✨it’s been a long time since I cook or bake due to work✨I’m sure quite a lot of you are adjusting and going back to the hustle routine as well😞💪but this is something you can do with zero cooking skills, brainless movements and serve it up super fast and beautifully!❤️

Ingredients:
▪️Unagi 🐟 (got mine from @shopee_sg @theseafoodcompany.sg flash deals - 3 large unagi for $34!) 
▪️Egg 🥚 
▪️rice 🍚 
▪️cucumber 🥒 
...
1) cook the rice using rice cooker, put the unagi on a plate and placed it on top of the rice during halftime.
2) cook the egg in boiling water for 7 mins, put it in ice water for 5 mins to get #onsenegg ! If not #hardboiledegg  look good too😂
3) cut the cucumber into slices or if u have a shredder just shred it into strips.
4) combine them all on top of the rice and serve!👍💕
...

image_desc: Photo shared by @thegatedreverb on August 12, 2020 tagging @visit_singapore, @nparksbuzz, @naturesocietysingapore, @fish, and @singapore.
text:
During #circuitbreakersg, we discovered that all the fish in this pond had likely been decimated by kingfishers, making it a dengue hazard.
.
But pet shops weren’t allowed to sell any “pets” then. They were however, said the uncle with a knowing nod, allowed to sell food for pets. And so we acquired a $1 plastic bag of #feederfish that were destined for a short life either due to dodgy genes or fulfilling their destiny as some pet’s #livefeeder lunch, whichever would be the earlier. 
.
“Don’t be too happy; will die soon ah,” said the petshop uncle cheerfully as he waved goodbye to me and the bag of #mollyfish.
.
Turns out they were rather tenacious #mollies, and instead of self-destructing after a few weeks, have flourished and even propagated.
.
No idea how the fry survived since the Internet says the fry need to be separated into a #breederbox or risk being eaten.
.
And actually, no idea what the mollies eat since we haven’t ever fed them. Hopefully, their omnivorous diet includes all extant mozzie larvae.
.
Could be an inspirational metaphor for tenacity in a time of pandemic, recession, job losses, world conflict, environmental crisis. Or could be a visual parallel of #Matthew6*. 
.
Now we need to acquire some algae dudes to clean those walls.
.
.
.
*
“Look at the birds of the air: they neither sow nor reap nor gather into barns, and yet your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not of more value than they?
And which of you by being anxious can add a single hour to his span of life?
And why are you anxious about clothing? Consider the lilies of the field, how they grow: they neither toil nor spin, yet I tell you, even Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.
But if God so clothes the grass of the field, which today is alive and tomorrow is thrown into the oven, will he not much more clothe you, O you of little faith?
Therefore do not be anxious, saying, 'What shall we eat?' or 'What shall we drink?' or 'What shall we wear?'
For the Gentiles seek after all these things, and your heavenly Father knows that you need them all.
But seek first the kingdom of God and his righteousness, and all these things will be added to you.” (Matthew 6:26-33)

💥Tips for Making Plank Easier and More Effective.
.
👉Start small by aiming 20 secs and challenge to go longer 60 secs, 90secs etc…
👉Enjoy & be in the zone!
👉Improve your plank technique
.
.
📌Pin or 📥Save this video and give it a try
💪You definitely will see the different!
.
.
⚠️𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗣𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗸 𝗼𝗻 𝗘𝗹𝗯𝗼𝘄𝘀⚠️
1️⃣Elbows should line up directly underneath your shoulders.
2️⃣Ground toes into the floor and squeeze glutes to stabilize your body. Your legs should be working, too
3️⃣Keep a neutral neck and spine.
4️⃣Create a straight, strong line from head to toes. Butt position. Typically, it's too high, which means the abs aren't getting worked as much as they should.
5️⃣Hold that position & Engage the mind in the movement experience
.
⚠️𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗛𝗶𝗴𝗵 𝗣𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗸⚠️
⭕The only different 
1️⃣*Shoulders, Elbows & Wrist align
💥☝️Improper hand positions, such as placing hands too far forward or too wide apart, can put additional pressure on your wrists
💥☝️Turning hands inward or outward can also cause wrist pain.
.
⚠️𝗣𝗿𝗼𝗽𝗲𝗿 𝗙𝗼𝗿𝗺 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗦𝗶𝗱𝗲 𝗣𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗸⚠️
1️⃣Lie on side with right forearm flat on the floor, elbow under shoulder, and both legs extended.
2️⃣Body should form a straight line from head to feet, which are either stacked or staggered.
3️⃣Don’t drop your neck - Stay neutral
4️⃣Your top hand can be on side of hip (easier) or reaching up to the ceiling (harder).
5️⃣Engage your core and lift hips up
.
⚠️𝗦𝗶𝗱𝗲 𝗽𝗹𝗮𝗻𝗸 𝗳𝗼𝗿 𝗺𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝘀𝘂𝗽𝗽𝗼𝗿𝘁⚠️
👉Place your hand 45 degree for more support
.
📌Remember to save this post and use it when you are doing your plank! 📌

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Chinatown, Singapore with @fergus_mcarthur.
text:
🔥What to do in Chinatown! 🔥
.
👉🏻Chinatown memang menjadi salah satu distrik yang digemari turis untuk dikunjungi. Nah, di Singapore sendiri juga ada Chinatown. Apa aja sih yang bisa kamu explore? SAVE postingan ini untuk panduan jalan-jalan kamu di waktu berikutnya ya!🥰👌🏻
.
1️⃣ Buddha Tooth Relic Temple
Selain kaya akan budaya, Vihara ini juga Instagrammable + FREE! Kamu tinggal keluar dari MRT Chinatown Exit A, ke padoga street, lurus hingga pertigaan, lalu belok kanan.
.
2️⃣ Chinatown Street Market
Sepanjang jalan: Pagoda Street, Trengganu Street, Sago Street, Smith Street kamu bisa menemukan banyak souvenirs hingga street food. Lewat Exit A MRT Chinatown, lalu menuju ke Pagoda Street
.
3️⃣ Maxwell food Center
Makanan murah pasti kamu bisa menemukannya di Hawker Center. Ada Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice yang super terkenal, lho! Hanya 700m dari Station MRT Chinatown.
.
4️⃣ Pinnacle@Duxton Skybridge
Ini adalah perumahan 50 lantai yang ada di 1 Cantonment Road. Kamu bisa ke sky-bridgenya di level 50 lho untuk  menikmati pemandangan singapore. Tiketnya hanya sekitar $ 6 per orang (menggunakan ez link).
.
🌟Apalagi spot yang kamu suka di Chinatown Singapore? Tell us in comments below!👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻
.
📸Photo by: @fergus_mcarthur 🙏🏻
.

image_desc: Photo by 🌈RainbowDiaries⭐️Shub in ❤ Home Sweet Home ❤ with @shub_sg, @socialmediamomsg, and @homelyconnect.
text:
💻🖱️🖥️ Work from Home First Hand Tips 🖥️🖱️💻

Under the #newnormal many of us are working from home full time or at least partially under staggered work arrangements. We all have appreciated some unlikely benefits of Lockdowns but at the same time, Working from Home is not that rosy especially for health 😒

Here are my 2 cents on making the most of the #wfhlife while maintaining health quotient high.
⬇️⬇️⬇️
📍FOLLOW THE ROUTINE - When we are #wfh there is natural tendency to slack. Since we don't have to get ready, commute and go to the office, we tend to get a bit casual about time. To avoid this slack, it's best that we follow some routine. Get up on time, have breakfast, take shower and look presentable for meetings sets the ball rolling for an active day. 
📍GET ADEQUATE SLEEP - Disruptions in the sleep time and duration has been one of the major challenges that I faced in the initial days of #circuitbreakersg . Just because we are at home doesn't means each night becomes #netflix night 😱 I have made it a point that I get at least 6-7 hours of #beautysleep even while WFH.
📍DRINK ENOUGH WATER and keep yourself hydrated - When I am at home, I tend to drink less H2O and that's not a good habit. So now what I ensure is that there is always my @thermos_singapore on my table. Water is life even during #wfhlife 
📍EAT MODERATELY - Working from home means snacking more and eating more ? Yes very much possible so to avoid become a balloon it's good that we control the tongue. Eat lesser quantity of food and include lots of #greens and #fibre 
📍MOVE - There's always a danger of becoming a couch potato that's prone to attract Weight gain, UTI, bloatedness, gastric and many more lifestyle diseases. So what I do is - go on long walks with my hubby, go for grocery shopping, go and sweat it out in condo gym at least a few times in a week. #moveitmoveit 
📍CREATE CONDUCIVE WORK FROM HOME ENVIRONMENT - If possible, get a separate room, comfortable chair and table and ergonomic devices like this laptop stand from @homelyconnect that helps me to keep #rightposture 
.
What's your mantra to keep fit while WFH? Share with me 💚
.
#rainbowdiaries #newnormal2020 #doyourbest
