image_desc: Photo by Vanessa Kou in Singapore with @soulsugarbakes.
text:
Having gone a little bananas over the many bakes I had bought last month, I completely forgot to post about @soulsugarbakes Banana-tastic Soul Box! At $25, each dessert box comes with 3 Soul Sugar Cookies, 3 Banana Bites, a levain New York-style Red Velvet Cookie, and a jar of Banana Pudding.

Pretty hefty, their Red Velvet cookie ⁣⁣breaks apart to yield a soft interior with generous chunks of white chocolate, a hint of cocoa and vanilla. A tad sweet (even for me), the richness of the molten chocolate after warming the cookie was slightly overwhelming to finish in one sitting. Hence, I would recommend sharing or perhaps balancing it with bites of their Soul Sugar Cookies.

A classic chocolate chip cookie done right, the Soul Sugar Cookies were made with brown butter and flaky sea salt. Soft and chewy, they were not too rich and the dash of salt really helped to accentuate the bits of chocolate studded in the bakes.

However, my favourite item was none other than their Banana Pudding which is marketed as the first of its kind in Singapore. Layered with Regal Marie biscuits, the chilled golden pudding was creamy, luscious and each spoonful brought back childhood memories of me dunking the exact biscuit into warm milo. Though the biscuits became soggy, the best part is having them absorb all the flavours and lending the dessert a pleasant vanilla taste. I could also get bits of mashed bananas in every bite and overall it wasn’t too sweet.

A close second after the pudding, the Banana Bites were really good too. The buttery muffins were surprisingly moist, light, fragrant, and best enjoyed warm. Mixed in with chocolate chips and shredded coconut, the banana flavour is less pronounced in comparison but had a great texture. The crunch from the coconut and the small pockets of sweetness from the chocolate was the icing on the cake.

Gigs are coming back! Hooray!! 🥳 Had a lot of emailing to do, proposals to write and schedules to change. So glad to be interacting with people again. 😊😊 
.
The dust of CB Phase 2 is settling, and I finally have enough headspace to paint. Hope you've been keeping well these past couple of weeks, 2020's such a wild ride. Stay safe, everyone. New works soon! ❤💙

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Autobahn Motors with @victor_zhuo.
text:
🔥Vending Machine Minuman? sudah biasa. Vending Machine Buku? Hmm.. boleh juga. Kalau Vending Machine MOBIL? Hah, mobil?😩🤣🤣
.
🚘 Ini adalah Car Vending Machine Terbesar di Southeast Asia! Disebut-sebut sebagai "mesin penjual mobil mewah terbesar di dunia", showroom penjual mobil bekas Autobahn Motors setinggi 15 lantai dan dapat menampung hingga 60 mobil mewah termasuk Ferrari dan Porsche. Showroom berteknologi tinggi Autobahn Motors ini terinspirasi dari tampilan mobil mainan Matchbox. Kamu bisa melihatnya di Kilang Road, Bukit Merah. Dalam rangka National Day Singapore, Car Vending Machine ini disulap menjadi warna merah-putih. Keren banget!😍👍🏻👍🏻
.
🌟Menggunakan tampilan layar sentuh yang terletak di lantai dasar gedung, kamu bisa lho memilih mobil yang kamu mau, kemudian akan dikendalikan sistem dalam waktu sekitar 1-2 menit hingga keluar dari machine. Wow!👏🏻👏🏻
.
📍Kilang Road, Bukit Merah
.
📸Photo by: @victor_zhuo thanks for tagging us!
.

text:
COVID19 has thrown us into unchartered territory. We understand that as a result, prolonged mental blocks, boredom, frustration, and even possible experiences of loneliness, stress, and anxiety start to creep up. 
.
.
On The Line is thus created to tide this period through with you. Together with a facilitator, On The Line serves as a live chat platform for you to work through any issues you may have at hand. We believe that all the solutions that you need lie inside you.
.
.
Choose to give us your name or remain anonymous. Together with you, we aim to offer a different perspective and shed some light on the topics you would like to address.
.
.
Come and say hi. Be it a short 2 min chat, a 15 min companionship, or a 30minute coaching session. We are here, on the line (be it battle line or online) with you.
.
http://theinsidespace.com/on-the-line
.
.

image_desc: Photo shared by The Nyonya Sisters on August 10, 2020 tagging @sleeloveforothers. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'THREE TIPS TO MAKING EXERCISE SIMPLE The Nyonya Sisters @THENYONYASISTERS'.
text:
Beginning an exercise program can be intimidating if you have never incorporated regular exercise before or if you haven’t engaged in regular exercise for an extended period of time. Here are three simple tips to incorporate an exercise plan into your TR90 program.

1. Start out easy. Gradually working into physical activity helps you avoid getting too burned out after the first time. Muscle soreness often accompanies novel physical activity, and easing into a new activity can help to prevent this discomfort. Try start out at 15 to 30 minutes for 3 to 5 days a week, and then gradually increase the intensity and frequency.

2. Have a plan and stick to it. Having a plan removes the guesswork from exercise. It becomes easier to accomplish if you already know what you are going to do and how long you are going to do it. Your daily schedule can become busy quickly, and scheduling physical activity into your daily routine ensures you don’t leave it out when time gets crunched.

3. Finally, pick an activity you enjoy. The more you dread the activity, the more likely you are to leave it out of your busy schedule. Walking or jogging enjoyable routes, aerobics or zumba classes, or bike riding are great ways to exercise in an enjoyable way. Whatever activity you select, consistency is the key. By being physically active 30 to 60 minutes most days of the week, it becomes easy to add the benefits of exercise to your weight management efforts.
.
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Kusu Island, Singapore with @killian.tran.
text:
🌟Siapa nggak percaya kalau ini di Singapore? Kusu Island terletak sekitar 5,6 Kilometer di selatan Singapura,  termasuk dari salah satu “The Southern Island” Singapura. Kusu berarti “Kura-Kura” dalam bahasa Hokkien☺️🙌🏻
.
🐢Kamu bisa mengunjungi Kusu Island saat ”Kusu Season” (sekitar bulan September-November) dan akan ada banyak orang yang pergi kesana untuk memberi penghormatan di Kuil Da Bong Gong. Di dalam kuil, kamu bisa melempar koin ke lonceng di tengahnya, lalu membuat permintaan☺️☺️
.
🥳Di Kusu Island juga terdapat 3 Kramat (kuil dalam bahasa melayu) di puncak sebuah bukit yang dipecaya akan memberikan kekayaan, kesehatan, dan kesuburan. Untuk ke tempat tersebut, kamu harus mendaki 152 tangga! Dan perlu diingat, kamu dilarang untuk menginap atau camping di pulau ini👌🏻
.
📍How to get there: Pulau Kusu dapat dicapai dengan kapal feri dari Marina South Pier sekitar harga SGD18 untuk 1 tiket pulang-pergi.
.
🌟Tertarik mampir ke Kusu Island? Tag & ajak teman kamu!
.
📸Photo by: @killian.tran
.

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 09, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'HOMEMADE PEPPER LUNCH RICE'.
text:
•RECIPE• Wanted to try using my grill pan for something different. I made my own Pepper Lunch! The  LO asked for salmon and the family loves it! I am going to try making with shabu beef the next time round. The sauce is enough for at least two rounds so you can store it in a bottle and refrigerate for next round! Swipe to see my sizzling pan! ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
• 5 cloves garlic, minced
• 1/4 onion, cut into small pieces
• 50ml soy sauce
• 50ml honey
• 2 tbsp oyster sauce
• 1tbsp slurry (1 tsp cornflour with 1 tbsp water)

METHOD:
1) Fry the garlic and onion till fragrant.
2) Add in the rest of the sauce and slurry and simmer for about 5 to 10 minutes till the onion softens.
3) Use a blender and blend the mixture till you get a smooth solution. Add the amount you like onto your rice.

image_desc: Photo by Belanja Eat in Singapore. May be an image of text that says 'Belanja Eat Need a FREE meal? IMPORTANT UPDATE Please read!'.
text:
It's been 4 months since we first launched Belanja Eat. We started this as a community-led initative, with the intention for it to serve as a stop gap for those in need of a meal during these tough times, while helping out our neighbourhood hawkers. Thank YOU for coming forward to get this going, you have shown us that kindness is still alive and well in our community.
From 10 Aug onwards, the Belanja Eat team will stop updating and monitoring of the Belanja Eat map and stall directory, our social media accounts, our email address and feedback form.
However, we do hope this initiative will still continue for as long as there are meals being Belanja-ed out there! If you know of others who need support beyond just a meal, do check out supportgowhere.gov.sg for available grants and funds for those hard hit by #Covid19 or otherwise.
***
IMPORTANT
For Belanja Eat stall owners:
- If you would like to continue with Belanja Eat after 10 August, please do! The Belanja Eat poster will still be available for download on our website.
 If you are still using the existing poster with the BE team contact details (QR code and WhatsApp number) at the bottom, please fold it down as they will no longer be monitored. Note that the BE team will not be updating the stall directory on our Belanja Eat map or any feedback support after 10 August.
- If you would like to stop Belanja Eat on 10 August, simply take down the Belanja Eat poster on 10 Aug, when you close for the day.
***
#belanjaeat #stayhomeforSG #StrongerTogether #payitforward #circuitbreakersg #mustwearmask

image_desc: Photo by Fawn Labs in Jewel Changi Airport with @pei02, @petriebelle, @cambriant, @christina_meiwei, and @eldredquek. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
Happy 55th Birthday Singapore. Be Strong, #Singapore. #foundernotes 

Being featured in this year's National Day Parade show as a protagonist and profile is a huge honor, something I had not expected when we started the "Bottle Project".

Since we returned to the lab in Phase 2 of #CircuitBreakerSG, I am hopeful for change. Change in our society and #Singapore because I have witnessed so much strength, graciousness and have seen so many acts of kindness from fellow Singaporeans. The acts of heroism and sacrifice from our frontline workers and essential workers motivates me everyday to see how and where we can contribute.

I always stress that our "Bottle Project" wouldn't have been if not for the COLLECTIVE efforts and contributions from the Community. Each and everyone of you who walked in to drop of 1 or 2 bottles. YOU contributed in the fight against #Covid-19.

So to all my fellow #Singaporeans, contribute in anyways we can, every little bit is part of a larger Collective effort that will help us rebuild our beloved country as we try to find our way out of this pandemic. #togetherwearestronger 

I am extremely humbled to lead an incredible team here at Fawn Labs. Team mates who have shown leadership, strength, humility and resilience. They have sacrificed their own time and sleep to support this vision of giving back because we have the lab and capability to contribute. The reason why I work so hard everyday since we decided on taking up "Bottle Project" during Covid-19 and other Sustainable projects is because I want to ensure voices like theirs is heard.

Here at Fawn Labs, we believe in building a safe environment to share and learn, a journey to empower each other and raise awareness on issues related to #Sustainability and #CleanBeauty. We want to impact communities with the right knowledge and we want to give back where we can. To start with a ripple and watch it grow into a wave and beyond.

To each and every #Fawnling who has supported and encouraged us through this period, I thank you from the bottom of my heart. We welcome all of you to come and join us on this journey.

Fawn Lab's Family: @eldredquek @cambriant @petriebelle @meiwei11 @pei02

text:
🎇This was the simple happiness of complete harmony with her surroundings, the happiness that ask for nothing, that just accepts, just breathes, just is. 🎆 Today is a joyous day in Singapore because it is Singapore’s birthday!!! When we were younger in primary school, National Day was a BIG thing because there is half day in school, school celebrations to watch and free gifts to take home. When we were in our teens, National Day become a happy day that we don’t have  to do school work and go to school! When we joined the workforce, National Day become a public holiday to sleep in and go out with friends. Now, National Day become a day to celebrate with family members. It become an occasion for family gathering. ❤️ In any case, I still managed to spend some time in the afternoon to prepare simple foodart of flying jets (using herseys chocolate mint wafers) and my favourite DayPlus Chocolate Orange Bun, and coffee stencil art of ❤️ and “SG”. Also showcasing my new gold cutleries and hydrangeas cup and saucer. 🥰🥰🥰 Happy birthday Singapore and We Love SG! ❤️

"Ai Jiak Ba Hu Mai?"
was probably the one of the most repeated questions I've heard during mealtimes in my growing up years. 🍽
(It means "want to eat meat floss or not?")
.
Being raised in a Teochew household by my grandparents, porridge was probably consumed at least 5 times a week. 
My grandmother, the head chef, thought that Ba Hu was a perfect companion to porridge, and it was undeniably so. 🤤
.
It was only after becoming a mother myself that I was introduced to healthier versions of Ba Hu - Salmon Floss & Tilapia Floss!
The benefits of fish need no further explanation👍.
Under @Eessentialsg, Mamacooks Fish Floss recently went through a facelift to bring to you a cuter, more compact and thicker box, 3 sachets per box! Simply drop a box into your bag and you're all set to go!
.
@Eessentialsg would like to gift 5 lucky winners, YES you read right, FIVE, a set of the following each:
1) Salmon Fish Floss (Seasoned for 9M+)
2) Tilapia Fish Floss (Seasoned for 9M+)
3) Tilapia Fish Floss (Unseasoned for 6M+)
.

I am very proud of this product.

Did this in Phase 1 for @mm2singapore 's "Love within" challenge! Though I didn't win, I am glad I can now share this! The way I feel about this film can't be changed by criticism and not winning, and I'm glad I've made something I felt genuinely proud of.

A huge thank you to those who helped me here and there with my artistic wants and my technical needs: @sheamisenmusic, @partybells_ @joshuachristiantan @kloudyclown, @haikelzambri. You guys helped elevate my film to this level and I'm so grateful.

This was a story I wanted to tell after hearing about a close friend's struggle. And I can't believe I pulled off this film almost entirely by myself with limited equipment, filmed on a phone, picking up editing skills along the way, acting directing, lighting and writing this piece.

The cherry on top of those struggles was being 1st AD and locations manager because I have 8 people living in my house( it's truly difficult) with loads of stuff lying around and I never would have thought I could pull this off.

Please do like and share this short film if you enjoy it! It goes a long way.

Music Composor: @sheamisenmusic 
V/O artiste: @partybells_

image_desc: Photo by Muiee メイ on August 08, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'im.ag YRUGL 不是每一天都那么美好 但【每一天] 都会有一些 美好 东西 存在'.
text:
3匹猫の飼主さん兼男友人から貰った手作りのブラウニーとチーズケーキ❣️嬉しい😆そして美味しい😋特にブラウニーはめちゃ濃くてしっとり❣️ローカルスーパーのNTUCでは🇸🇬建国記念日で期間限定のBuy 1 get 1 Freeを行い，友人がPrimatTasteブランドのラブラックペーパー蟹🦀ソース入りのインスタントヌードルを買い、お裾分けに貰いました〜ラクサとカレーヌードルはかなり高い評判ですが、ブラックペッパーはどうだろう？めちゃ辛かったです…涙も出ました😂 私向けでは無いですが、辛い好きなの方は好きだと思います❗️お礼に又サツマイモ黒ごま食パンを焼き、ミートローフと一緒に友人へ渡しました❣️ここ数日は暑くて夕焼けが綺麗で空が真っ赤〜先程は薄い紫色の空が見えました❣️.
,
明日はシンガポール🇸🇬の55年建国記念日です〜今年の花火🎆は10箇所のHDB辺りに上げる予定で、我が家の地域も選ばれました❣️場所は公布して無いので、窓から見えたら良いね❣️.
.
皆さん良い週末を❣️Stay Safe 😷.
.
.
三只猫的主人兼朋友送来的Brownie和Cheese Cake ❣️好 好吃😋 他说今次做的Brownie有达到他要的口感、浓度和湿度 做得很成功👍 真的叻 太好吃了👏👏👏 芝士蛋糕也好吃到、完全不輸外面卖的叻👏👏👏.
.
前陣子NTUC 有Buy 1 get 1 offer 友人送我2包Black pepper crab口味的即食麵、初品尝今天煮來試試....
还滿辣一下的叻 立即飙泪😂. 也把烤好的番薯黑芝麻吐司和meatloaf 当作回礼送过去给友人.
.
这几天的天气很热😵💦 很常見火燒云日落🌄 今天还见到紫色天空呢！明天是新加坡🇸🇬的55周年国庆日、今年的国庆庆典烟花汇演分散10个地点燃放、我这区有被選中 希望能從窗戶可以见到烟花🎆呀！.
.
㊗️大家周末愉快！假日快樂！Stay Safe 💪🏻.
.

The gym is once again picking up some really good momentum. As more and more of you are coming back, we just want to remind the community to keep following the rules so we can keep providing you with a happy and safe environment to work out in. We hope you understand that rules aren’t always the easiest or fun but we need to enforce them to ensure all gyms across Singapore remain open! #SGunited.
➡️ Please only come up the stairs 5 minutes before the start of class to prevent overcrowding 
➡️ Please do not wait in the stairwell, only outside before class
➡️ When you walk in, come to the front desk to get your temperature checked and show your Check in code to the front desk
➡️ Make sure we are maintaining a safe distance from everyone at all times, before, during and after our sessions.
➡️ Our showers and change rooms are still closed, so please make sure you find an alternate solution.
➡️ If you have your own equipment such as gloves, wraps and skipping ropes, please bring to every class.

image_desc: Photo by Anu Anand on August 08, 2020. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
Grilled Chicken
When you see a whole grilled chicken on my feed, it means "I am not in the mood to cook, but I want good food". I have seldom made grilled chicken as a special dish, its always been a quick thing where it takes 5-10 min to marinate, and the rest of the work is done by the oven 😆 But if the marination is reasonably ok, you get a good meal.
This one ... stuffed it with carrot, potato, lemongrass, onion, ginger, garlic. Marinated in lemon juice, ginger-garlic paste, my favourite 5 spice powder, salt, honey and a tbsp of youghurt to bring all the ingredients together.
.
.
.
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by Chop Chop Biryani & Meats in Amoy Street Food Centre.
text:
Siew Yoke (Cantonese dialect) is often referred to as roasted pork belly, but better known as 烧肉 or siobak to many others.

A pretty tedious process every morning - perfecting the roast and battling with the heat each time. Slabs of pork bellies are roasted till the skin is charred and then scraped off to reveal the golden-brown crispiness before chopping into serving portions.

Makes it worthwhile when returning customers complimented us on it ☺️
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo shared by Vanessa Kou on August 07, 2020 tagging @snackit.sg.
text:
Complete with real fruit bits, Meng Niu Yoghurt Drinks (蒙牛真果粒花果轻乳) come in two lovely floral-fruity blends. Though the drinks were of low-viscosity, they didn’t taste diluted as the flavours were pretty prominent. My favourite being the Sakura & White Peach, packed in blue, as upon the first sip I could taste the hint of floral followed by the delicate sweetness of peach. The tanginess of the yoghurt was also more of an aftertaste. In pink, the Rose & Strawberry was slightly sweeter in my opinion, and tasted a tad artificial to me. However, it is a good pick for those who don’t usually enjoy the sourness of yoghurt and was light overall with a nice balance of the key ingredients.

To order, DM @ snackit.sg. 1 carton (10 bottles) is priced at $28 (+$5 courier) while 2 Cartons (20 bottles) goes for $50 with free courier service where you can mix the flavours.

text:
Weekend lunch ideas 💡 
Thanks @yvonnemsw for sharing her secret recipe to everyone 👍🏻

📞Order smoked duck at www.foodsomania.com

#Repost @yvonnemsw 
・・・
【 Recipe 】Creamy Lemon Penne with Mushroom & Smoked Duck

Been thinking of Pasta al Limone after seeing @thekitchenettetales Angie's post last week. Haven't had this almost forgotten flavour for a long long while. And yes 🙋‍♀️ I support her to include pasta as breakfast staple because Pasta is Life 😆

Sharing another under 30-min recipe here.
🍝 Bring a pot of water to a boil. Add salt & pasta. Cook pasta according to the timing indicated on the packet. Drain well & reserve some of the pasta water.
🍝 Melt butter with olive oil in a pan. Sear the duck breast skin side down till crisp. Flip over and cook for another couple of minutes or so. Remove & let it rest for a while before slicing thinly.
🍝 Using the same pan sauté mushrooms until slightly softened, add chopped garlic. Stir fry till the garlic turns light brown before pouring in cooking cream.
🍝 Let it simmer for a little before adding lemon zest & juice. Add cheese and let it thicken slightly.
🍝 Add the cooked pasta, freshly chopped parsley, sea salt, black pepper and a few tablespoons of pasta water (if required). Mix well to coat the pasta evenly.

Original/Black Pepper Smoked Duck from @Foodsomaniasg is selling at $5 for 200-220g. Head over to foodsomania.com for your online quality grocery shopping. Free delivery for purchase above $60 and receive free gift for payment made via Paynow.

image_desc: Photo by Unapologetically Amanda Koh on August 07, 2020.
text: During the 3 months of the CB, this was a view I thought about, when Fitness First said they were going to dissolve the existing schedule and that there would be changes to the routine that had been ours for years. As a freelance yoga teacher for the last 15 years, we find ourselves in situations like these every now and then, but in my entire lifetime in this, it’s never been as drastic and long drawn out as 2020 has been. I have learnt to embrace the fact that class cancellations are not in fact, a loss of income, but that a predictable source of income has been disrupted, and that I have the freedom to create new ways to manifest what I need. I have learnt that no matter how long I have had classes on schedule or students, that they are not my classes and that I do not have ownership of my students or their practice. I have also taught long enough to know that the ones who find connection, will find their way back if we are meant to journey together again. I have learnt that newness always presents itself, and to be ready to let go to allow the new in, and for that to happen, I have to constantly evolve to serve the purpose that is my life’s work. The way I teach today is almost completely different from what I was doing at the beginning of my journey, and yes, I see myself doing this probably for the rest of my life. I have had to start from scratch several times over, and each time teaches me that in evolving, I grow resilience, calmness and clarity. #singaporeyoga #2020vision #fitnessfirstsg #sgyoga #tittibhasana #sunset #fusionopolis #circuitbreakersg #lifein2020 #resilience #weareinthistogether #yoga

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 06, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'TOMYUM SEAFOOD STEW'.
text:
•RECIPE• Ran out of idea what to cook and the hubb says: Clear the fridge! Got a pack of tomyum herbs and I made Tom yum stew! So good and easy for a comforting dinner. See IG video for the steps :) ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
• A packet of Tom Yum herbs from @fairpricesg
• 1. 5 tbsp tomyum paste
• Cooking cream
• 1 tomato, cut into 4 slices
• A packet of bunashimeiji
• 2 tbsp fish sauce
• Seafood of your choice

METHOD:
1) Fry the lemongrass, shallots and galangal in a little oil till fragrant
2) Add in tomato and mushroom and fry for another minute
3) Add in tomyum paste and enough water to cover all the herbs and boil over high heat for 10 minutes. 
4) Add in more water and bring to boil. Add in the seafood. 
5) Continue to simmer for another 5 to 10 minutes. Add some cooking cream to thicken it. Season to taste with some fish sauce. 
6) Drizzle some lime juice. Serve hot.
============================================================ #tomyum #tomyumsoup #seafood #30minutemeals #30minutesrecipe #simple #sgig #sgrecipes #sgfoodie #sgfoodies #sgfoodstep #instagfoodsg #singaporehomecooks #homecookedmeals #whati8today #instagfoodsg #家常便饭 #sgfoodlover #onepotmeal #comfortfoods #circuitbreakersg

image_desc: Photo shared by 365days2play and EAT! on August 06, 2020 tagging @crappysotong, @eileen_eats_alot, @changiairport, @visit_singapore, @hungrygowhere, @beautifulcuisines, @paradisegrpsg, @jewelchangiairport, @sgfoodfinder, and @brandcellar.
text:
My first time checking out Paradise Classic at Jewel. The restaurant serves mainly Singapore and Malaysian zi char mainstays. I must say the dishes we tried were all very good. Very homely and comforting fare and I'm already making plans to bring my parents to try the food as I write this.
.
These are the items we tried, and they are only available for a limited period, which is a pity because though ought to be mainstays!
- Pan-fried Vermicelli with Assorted Seafood $16.80
- Stewed Roasted Pork with Diced Chilli in Claypot $16.80
- Stir-fried La-La in Curry Sauce $16.80
- Seafood Paradise Signature Creamy Butter Crab $88
.
The fried vermicelli is definitely a must try. Love the smoky savoury flavour of the gravy and the texture of the noodles. A dish well done. And the crab! Some will not like the sweet butter sauce but I loved it. I had 3 bowls of that sauce and I polished off 3 mantous too. The crab was sweet and succulent too, and the flesh came out easily. If not for the pricing, I would love to have this again.
.
🍴Paradise Classic
📍78 Airport Blvd, #04 - 244, Singapore 819666
@ParadisegrpSG

I’m really blessed that after the looooong #CircuitBreakerSG, I am packed with appointments with my friends, existing clients and their referrals. 

A little snippet of what a young prospect in his early 20s told me when we are discussing his financial priorities and how he want to allocate his money, “you can be young without money, but you can’t be old without it. I have seen friends of my parents suffer because of the lack of retirement planning and I’m super glad that my parents did. Hence I want to follow their footsteps and ensure I don’t burden anyone in future.”

He said that in front of his dad while we were discussing his needs and wants. The proud yet humble smile on the dad’s face was etched in my memory and I’m really really touched by how mature he thinks. 

P.S. if you are keen to know what I’ve been sharing, dm me to find out 😛

#ProudDad #BePosiTiff

image_desc: Photo shared by @magicmoistness on August 06, 2020 tagging @fazleen.jpg, @_fionaseow, and @tinypangolin.
text: “flat”, as a project, holds a special place in my heart - if only because it came out of a particularly low point in life (both mine and everyone else’s). The worse things seemed to get, with the world falling apart at the seams, the more it seemed that we should just screw this shit and see if we can experiment. I wasn’t exactly sure what the final product was going to look like, but here we are, and oddly enough, the show has already begun to take on a commemorative aspect for me - a memento mori, a signifier of how close we all came to the other side, for a while back there ... It’s the last weekend of the show, swing by! (And before I forget, muchas gracias once again to the artists, and @meganarlin .) #flat #sgcb #singapore #contemporaryart #white #monochromatic #singaporeart #singaporeartist #circuitbreakersg #lifeduringcovid19

image_desc: Photo shared by S A B R I N A 📷 S I K O R A on August 06, 2020 tagging @hm, @dillards, @celson.sg, @badgerandfoxsingapore, and @mabeapparel. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
Feels like we have been home all year! Very thankful for this little urban jungle on my balcony. 🌿🌵.
.
.
.
All this time at home has caused me to do a massive clean out and reevaluate spots that I never really used before. My husband would always so sit out here but I always found it too buggy and uncomfortable. I added a few lanterns with bug repellent candles, two large comfy chairs at the other end of the balcony, and a few more fun accessories and 💥(boom) instant upgrade! How gorgeous is this rug?! Now we are both out here every night after the kids go to sleep chatting or meme-sharing the night away. So happy I was introduced to @celson.sg and their gorgeous furniture and accessories range. What can I decorate next? 
.
.
.
Rug and lanterns (new collection) @celson.sg 
Skirt (new collection) @mabeapparel available at @badgerandfoxsingapore 
Shirt (old) @dillards 
Necklace (old) @hm .
.
.

Now I just need a tall plant stand to replace this stool! Any ideas for where to find that?

image_desc: Photo by Sheryl -Food & Travel Blogger🌎 in Singapore with @sherbakes. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
🍚A Super FLAVOURFUL VERSION OF Japanese Fried Rice 🍚 Do you know that adding Kewpie Japanese mayo to the rice before frying makes the taste richer. It also separates the grains so you end up getting those grains well coated with the egg and ingredients you fry them together with ❤️💯💯⁣
⁣
Ingredients:⁣
1 cup cooked rice⁣
1-2 tbsp kewpie Japanese mayo⁣
Spam/ham, chopped into cubes⁣
1 tbsp olive oil ⁣
2 eggs, lightly beaten⁣
1 tbsp soy sauce⁣
Chopped spring onions⁣
⁣
Steps:⁣
1)Mix the rice with the mayo ⁣
2)In a frying pan under medium heat, fry the spam until skin is slightly crispy⁣
3)Move spam to one side of the pan and add oil to the other side⁣
4)Add in beaten eggs and cook, scrambling them along the way⁣
5)Add in rice and mix everything together⁣
6)Add in soy sauce and taste. Add more if not salty enough⁣
7)Add in spring onions and mix⁣
8)Serve warm and top with seaweed (optional)⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣

🌟Selama masa Circuit Breaker (sama seperti PSBB di Indonesia), semua tempat wisata, pusat perbelanjaan, bahkan kolam renang tidak diizinkan beroperasi. #SGB_Family yang tinggal di Singapura pun tidak boleh keluar rumah.
.
✅ Setelah dua bulan berlalu dan Covid-19 mulai bisa dikendalikan, akhirnya Singapura masuk ke Fase 2. Di fase ini beberapa bisnis boleh beroperasi. Hotel dan tempat wisata juga sudah dibuka dan bisa dikunjungi oleh pengunjung lokal. Dirgan akan membagi sehari perjalanannya di Singapura dengan protokol kesehatan yang baru, untuk kamu yang sudah rindu #KangenSingapura, dan tetap terinspirasi saat merencanakan liburanmu!😜☺️
.
🌟Penasaran bagaimana Singapura setelah masa Circuit Breaker (PSBB)? Bagaimana protokol keamanan dan kebersihannya? Pastikan #SGB_Family nggak ketinggalan dan tonton sampai habis karena bakalan ada Give Away!🔥🔥
 .

HOW OFTEN TO TRACK WEIGHT
In general, you should weight yourself about once a week or every other week. If you are trying to lose weight once a week is best. If you weigh yourself too often you may be discouraged by normal fluid shifts. It is best to weigh yourself in the morning, before breakfast ✌🏻😍

image_desc: Photo by TSA • CEO OF MIQUEEN.CO in Singapore. May be an image of text that says '1 い'.
text:
Ever since the start of Circuit Breaker, I realised so much about myself. Recently, I chopped my pocket & took that courage to purchase an apple pencil which I always wanted even knowing that I've zero talent in drawing. I started with a blank space with nothing in my mind & I asked myself - why did I even spent this money to buy this stupid pencil. 😡 I felt demoralised because no matter how I tried to pen down that image in my mind, it just comes off with nothing. 😅 But I believe that as long as you're willing to learn, nothing is actually impossible? As least that's what I believed & has been keeping me going so far. So since I've no talent in drawing, I decided to go for YouTube where many talented artists posted their artworks or even best; TUTORIAL! 🙈 So I was browsing through & came across this YouTube video by @makoccinos. It was easy to follow & I managed to come out with a slightly better piece than ever. 💜 Drawing is really very relaxing for me & I really hope I could improve better the next round.

text:
🌻... the most beautiful smiles in the world are the ones that struggle through the tears.🌻 Crying is not a weakness. It is just a way of relieving stress. What’s important is the courage to continue and persevere on after crying and the courage to smile after crying. 😊 Today I made an effort to sneak out at 10.40am to buy from the Toast Box Kopivan. Again, some hot food items are already sold out! 😱 Still, I managed to buy dry Mee Siam, Pork Floss Toast and a few Pork Floss buns that have just arrived.  The buns are really soft and nice. I wish this Kopivan comes once a week! 🤣 Then I recreated my food into a beautiful lady. I just drew the facial features, so I don’t know who this person is. 🤣 Just a pretty lady who is smiling through her teary eyes? Finally we are approaching end of week soon.... everyday is getting a little more weary than before. I need to figure it out soon. 💪💪💪

image_desc: Photo shared by Not a Tastemaker. on August 05, 2020 tagging @nikvoon, and @patricoantonio.
text:
• A S S A M  F I S H  H E A D  C U R R Y •

It’s not everyday that @nikvoon and my cravings intersect, so when they do, I definitely make it count. Nik: “Hmmm fish head curry sounds good” Pat: “Done”.
.
.
.
My inner uncle gets a huge kick out of buying fresh whole fish over the counter from the fish monger. Nothing beats the value of a whole fresh fish. The selection that day was a little limited but I managed to get my hands on a nice medium-sized white snapper as well as a slightly larger grouper head. I’m the only one in my household who actually eats the heads in fish head curry, so more for me!
.
.
.
The distinct tang of the Assam lifts and cuts through the rich curry which was balanced out with a smidge of grated palm sugar (instead of plain ol’white cane sugar) for an added depth of sweetness - a worthwhile experiment. This curry goes great with fluffy white rice and some freshly fried up papadum for good measure (this isn’t an Indian curry, but why not right?).
.
.
.
Fun fact: Nyonya style Assam Fish Head Curries don’t use any kind of milk/dairy, but instead they use toasted jasmine rice that’s grounded fo a fine powder.
.
.
Made by me, shot by him.

image_desc: Photo by Sayuri (さゆり) 🇸🇬 on August 05, 2020.
text:
#FoodieQuestInLockdown Part 5 🙆‍♀
.
A somewhat normal life resumes but I'm determined to eventually showcase all of my meals during Circuit Breaker ! 😬
.
Good stuff, Good stuff! 💖
.
Day 28: Duck Mee ! (This brings queue every day here in Bangkit Road and they close really early in the afternoon. It's literally the only time I accept Yellow Noodles. The secret is in its sauce, tender duck meat and chilli! 😍😍😍)
.
Day 29 : @pizzaboysg and @dessertstorysingapore ( I'm quite a fan of pizzaboy's garlic pizza and hawaiian pizza! It's also the first time we ordered in desserts during CB!) 😋
.
Day 30: Wanton Mee from Bangkit Road ( Absolutely delicious!! Its QQ alkaline noodles drenched in slightly starchy sauce.) 🥰
.
Day 30 dinner : air-fried fish, cabbage and thai chilli fish with rice! (Home cooking!) 😝
.
Day 31 : Yong Tau Foo with Dry Noodles @kookeeyongtowfoomee . (Oho, another noodles. This one had me at its hakka style transparant sauce! I could have 3 bowls of these noodles. YTF here is standardized.) 🤗
.
Day 32: Tonkotsu Ramen from @tagakiramen !! ( This is where my first love for ramen begun years back! Economical, no frill, well made broth~) 🥰🥰
.
Day 33: 4 Dishes "Point Point Rice" with cabbage, spinach, sweet and sour pork and steamed egg! ( I must have been really hungry ) 😆
.
.
.
Wow. That was a combo of good food days! 😝
.
What's next? 🙆‍♀

text:
“I’m most comfortable in my birthday suit.” 😝

.
When you can’t fit into most of your clothes, take ‘em off. 😂 While some of you turned into lean, mean exercising machines during #circuitbreakersg, I turned into a recipe-churning, cooking machine. 👩🏻‍🍳 I put all of my time, effort & energy into #cherylwritesacookbook, released a smaller ebook version of @smitteninthekitchen which raised $12,700 for @foodfromtheheartsg & totally stopped working out. 😭 Moving forward, I promise to take better care of myself & find a better balance between work, play, food & fitness. How have you been coping with juggling it all? 💋

I think it’s a spiritual understanding of real joy within you. Anyway, today is an exciting day for the property as we welcome the Toastbox Kopivan into our premises. Since 9am, I kept peeping out from my balcony at the ordering queue to the food van. Finally at 11.50am, I sneaked out to queue. By the time it reaches me, everything is sold out except sandwiches, drinks and Tau Sah Piahs. 😱 So I bought 2 sets of ala carte Kaya Toast and 2 Tau Sah Piahs and my collection number is 164! Business is brisk! The van is here for another day tomorrow and I MUST queue earlier for more food options! Anyway, presenting my Toast Box food items with foodart of their TBKopivan. 🤩 Wish me luck tomorrow!

text:
まだ ロックダウン時期の6月にシンガポールのNational Parksが”Gardening with Edibles” となうプログラムを開催し、自宅で野菜を栽培したい住民に種を配るキャンペーンを行い、やっと今日にその種が届きました〜種はランダム配りで、我が家はオクラとほうれん草を貰いました〜オクラは植える場所によって我が家に難しいので、ほうれん草からにしました〜🌱が咲くかな〜期待しています❣️.
.
皆さん良い日を❣️Stay Safe 💪🏻.
.
在Lockdown期间、新加坡国家公园局(NParks) 为了提高粮食供应、鼓励有兴趣的居民种植蔬菜🥬. 之前上网申请后终于在今天收到了！收到洋角豆和菠菜的种子、然而洋角豆在目前的家不夠地方难种植、试先从菠菜开始～希望几天后见其犮芽、期待也！.
.
㊗️大家 周三 工作愉快！平安健康 💪🏻.
.

image_desc: Photo shared by 365days2play and EAT! on August 04, 2020 tagging @burpple, @huffposttaste, @visit_singapore, @gastrogig, @hungrygowhere, @chefshentan, @beautifulcuisines, @straitstimesfood, @eloquence.sg, @savefnbsg, @dineathomesg, and @thankgoodnessits.
text:
Gastrogig, a local events and gastronomic curator has recently launched Thank-Goodness-It’s (TGI), a delivery-only pop-up concept that will change its offerings every 2 months. This first edition of TGI features Chef Shen Tan’s Nasi Lemak from Shen's days at Maxwell Food Centre. Available on www.tginasilemak.com till 30 August 2020, the familiar flavours of her Nasi Lemak are further enhanced with produce from Gastrogig’s 350sqm garden, which make up the bulk of the raw ingredients for the rempah of the rendang dishes. 
*
Featured here (swipe right) is the $88 Makan for 4 set, comprising:
+ Twice Steamed Nasi Lemak Rice + Omelette + Ikan Bilis + Rainbow Pickles + 2 types Sambals
+ Choice of Chicken or Beef Rendang
+ Choice of Crispy Chicken or Crispy Pork Belly 
+ Choice of Sambal Goreng or Sambal Eggplant
+ Dessert: 2 Pieces Pulut Hitam Cake + Gula Melaka Butterscotch
+ Dessert: 2 Pieces Double Valrhona Choc Fudge Cake 
*
Super love the beef rendang! Such robust flavours. I had it for leftovers again the next day and it was still good. Wish I could have tried the pork belly. Desserts good too! Those of you who like sambal will also want to check out the coffee sambal, yes you heard me right. Bottled sambals are also available for order.
*
@tginasilemak
@gastrogig 
@chefshentan
@eloquence.sg

SALUTE THE MOON⠀
This is a variation of a moon salutation that I love to practice in the evenings, during the new moon, full moon, during menstruation or when I'm low on energy but still want to moon. With no 'vinyasa's, it's a little less energetic, but extremely nourishing and adequately stimulating for the body. ⠀
By incorporating standing postures (triangle, goddess, star) it's still fairly grounded; by including asanas close to the ground (low lunge, skandasana) it allows you to connect with the draw of gravity. As you're moving through the flow, notice any areas of unnecessary effort, and using your exhales, release and yield to the draw of the earth. Hope you enjoy :)

text:
久々にこちらのパークを訪ねました、シンガポールで珍しい湿地保護地区スンガイブロウ(Sungai Buloh) 、特に毎年の9月から3月までは、寒さから逃れて温暖な気候のオーストラリアに向かう途中の渡り鳥がこちらで羽を休み、有名なバードウォッチング名所です. 今回は反対側に増加した海岸コースで散策、初心者や子供も楽しめるコースです〜運が良ければオオトカゲ、ワニやカワウソが見えます🤣 ちなみに海岸コースではマレーシアのジョホールバルが近くにも見えます❗️
.
好久沒来坐落在北部Kranji的Sungai Buloh 湿地保护区
由其是每年的9月至三月是候鳥遷徙的季节
这时期到访可以见到不少候鳥在此休息
今次沒去观鳥的步道Buloh Tidal Ponds
而前往另一向的紅樹林步道 coastal trail 散步去
好运的话 可以见到Monitor Lizard, 水獺和鰐魚等
另外从Coastal Trail也能见到對岸马來西亞的Johor Bahru
鸟巢型的休息亭設計 相當吸睛也是IG打卡的景点.
.

text:
🎀𝐆𝐈𝐕𝐄𝐀𝐖𝐀𝐘🎀
"Ai Jiak Ba Hu Mai?"
was probably the one of the most repeated questions I've heard during mealtimes in my growing up years. 🍽
(It means "want to eat meat floss or not?")
.
Being raised in a Teochew household by my grandparents, porridge was probably consumed at least 5 times a week. 
My grandmother, the head chef, thought that Ba Hu was a perfect companion to porridge, and it was undeniably so. 🤤
.
It was only after becoming a mother myself that I was introduced to healthier versions of Ba Hu - Salmon Floss & Tilapia Floss!
The benefits of fish need no further explanation👍.
Under @Eessentialsg, Mamacooks Fish Floss recently went through a facelift to bring to you a cuter, more compact and thicker box, 3 sachets per box! Simply drop a box into your bag and you're all set to go!
.
@Eessentialsg would like to gift 5 lucky winners, YES you read right, FIVE, a set of the following each:
1) Salmon Fish Floss (Seasoned for 9M+)
2) Tilapia Fish Floss (Seasoned for 9M+)
3) Tilapia Fish Floss (Unseasoned for 6M+)
.
To stand a chance to win, simply:
1) Follow @Eessentialsg and @venetia.ngin
2) Like this post
3) Tag one friend per comment
4) Share this post to your IGS & tag us both for additional chances to win. [Optional]
Good luck! 🤞
Contest ends on 10 Aug 2020 at 1200.
Winners will be chosen at random and announced on the same day!
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Kampong Glam, Singapore with @adventurefaktory. May be an image of text that says 'Kampong Glam'.
text:
🔥4 Lokasi Mural Fenomenal! 🤘🏻😋
.
1️⃣ Indian Mural @ Kampong Glam
Mural bertema suku Indian kayak foto diatas pasti sering kamu lihat di socmed. Lokasinya berada di dekat jalan utama, membuat mural di Haji Lane, Kampong Glam ini mudah untuk ditemui!
.
2️⃣ Coffee Story @ Near A.R.C
Bergambar  bapak – bapak arab lagi bikin teh tarik, ada uncle – uncle yang rebus kopi dan ada anak anak nuangin espresso. Mural yang ini berada di sisi tembok sebuah coffee shop bernama A.R.C. Buat nyari mural ini kayaknya lebih gampang cari A.R.C dulu, baru ngintip ke tembok di depannya. Lokasi A.R.C ada di 29 Sultan Gate.
.
3️⃣ Satay Club @ Kampong Gelam
Kalaupas lagi lewat Jalan Sungai Pinang nggak akan kelewat sih karena warnanya cerah dan lukisannya lumayan besar. Adanya tepat di depan Hotel Nuve. Lukisannya ada 2 tema, yang satu tentang keluarga yang lagi makan satai ramai-ramai dan di sebelahnya ada tukang satai juga.
.
4️⃣ Treehouse @ Jalan Sultan
Gambarnya berupa pohon dengan deretan ayam di pojok bawah. Yang ini mungkin agak jarang keliatan. Lokasinya memang nggak jauh dari hostel 5footway inn Bugis. Tepatnya di Jalan Sultan yang dekat persimpangan dengan Beach Road.
.
👉🏻Kampong Glam adalah perpaduan yang indah antara sejarah dan budaya dengan pemandangan trendi. Banyak art street warna warni dan dipenuhi banyak toko!🥰
.
🔥🔥Kalau Mural Favoritmu dimana? Tell us in comment below!👇🏻👇🏻
.
📸Photo by: @adventurefaktory 
.

image_desc: 2 Meats Biryani Set (Siew Yoke + Pork Masala)
text:
Washing, drying, and storing of plates and utensils were one of the many challenges we faced at the stall. Things got worse when the cleaning service fee doubled their pricing back in 2018. We were forced to make the change to use disposable plates and utensils instead.

Of course, we too understood the importance of sustainability and the pollution caused using plastic packaging daily but then came Covid-19, and everyone viewed single-use packaging as a better packaging alternative from a hygiene point of view. We were actively sourcing for a sustainable option but prices for most eco-friendly packaging were not very pocket friendly for us. 

But today, we are happy to share that we found THE option! Using new sugar cane fibre boxes that don’t cost the earth each time you indulge in our biryani 😉 We also encouraged customers to bring their container to enjoy takeaway discounts at the stall and help reduce the use of plastic packaging on earth.

Tiny steps to help make the world a better place. What do you guys think?
.
.
.

image_desc: Photo by Phoebe 피비 in Singapore.
text:
The prizes are ready for collection! As you've realized, this time I gave prizes to every participating student! I used to give prizes to the top performers of each category in the past concerts I've organized,  but I realized that there are some students who are just way stronger than others and they keep getting the prizes. This has led to some of my students being discouraged as they have also put in effort - one of them cried when she reached home after the previous concert. So, this time, instead of rewarding students according to how well they have played for the concert, I decided to award them according to their individual strengths and efforts. In my studio, there is no best or favorite student. You are all my favourite. 😄👍🏻
.

.
Y小姐的個案正正符合編所說的，Y小姐在一個月前開始飲用CM LESS修身系列，雖然體重只下降了1.7公斤，大約3.75磅，卻完美對付頑固肚腩😍，輕鬆變回平坦的小腹。不忌吃，不運動，亦能有如此效果！（編還是建議大家保持適量運動，效果更佳喔😎😎！）
.

image_desc: Photo shared by S A B R I N A 📷 S I K O R A on August 02, 2020 tagging @shopping_at_tiffanys, @sachdeva.ritika, @sceptrcosmetics, and @houseofrajput. May be an image of 1 person.
text:
No Monday blues thanks to this jumpsuit! 💙
.
.
.
Things are starting to look up in Singapore and I’m pretty hopeful for the rest of the year. Not hopeful about travel back home to the USA, as any leisure travel still seems many months away, but just hopeful that we won’t need to lockdown again. Masks are mandatory here and we check into everywhere we go with our ID and a QR code. It took a while to get used to and get the kids onboard with mask-wearing (kids above the age of two need to wear them) but they were pretty excited about their storm trooper face shields and are used to all the hand washing and sanitizing. We can have up to five people in our house so play dates are back on which has been a game changer for the kids. They love being able to see their friends, and frankly I love getting to see mine. Things are slower but that’s actually been a really nice change. After that 145 day stretch at home, our family is relishing these little victories. 
.
.
.

During the CB period, I sang with this amazing group of people - virtually, with a local arts group cum community choir known as Syncroony.
.
🎙Singing 🎶 is what we do and what we love 💘 and the outpour of support and care as part of this cosy little group has always been so incredible. 🥰🥰
.
It also was a pleasure to help piece together this little video of us, highlighting the theme of relying on each other during this time of need. 💕 Count on Me was such an apt song, a truly heartwarming project to embark on. It perfectly added some colour to an otherwise darker period of time, like an anchor in a storm. ⚓ 🌊 🌧 🌩
.
Here's a snapshot of the video. Am proud to also say that it has been "immortalised" into the NLB archives as well! 😍😍
.
🔊SOUND ON
👁 and spot me! ;)
.
For the full video, do tap into @syncroony 's page 💖 and follow us if you'd like to see more ☺💕
.
.

✨💕@kkisweets finally reopened at Seah street!💕✨ I always remember my first visit to their SOTA Branch craftholic collaboration which was one of a kind and a memorable cafe experience☺️ this time round, their new concept of a curated dessert restaurant really elevated and lived up to the kki experience from ambience design to the delicate palate❤️💡CHECK MY INSTAHIGHLIGHT FOR MORE DETAILS, SWIPE FOR SECTIONS!💡❤️
...
▫️ Teh ($9.50) 
This is the MUST GET👍 the earl grey mousse with pear puree core and hazelnut crack is just a perfect balance from the smooth fragrant tea to the bite of savory pear and crunch of nutty sweetness✨ 
▫️ “J” ($13.50)
This “pot of plant” is specially made from a customized bake mold which really tells you their passion and attention to their craft🥰the base of black sesame made of kantan jelly, filled with matcha, yuzu and chocolate soil is just all japanese dessert lovers’ dream come true🌿✨
▫️Koide ($10.50)
This pastel beauty is made from pink grapefruit mousse set on mint sponge filled with lychee mousse and grapefruit jelly🌸 this is definitely edible art defined✨ the bitter sweet citrus combi is wow👍
▫️ Fromage ($13.50)
Lastly, the final flavor punch🤜 this is cheese is all textures 🧀 that added kick from the rum infused fruits 🍾 a dessert for the “rich”😂
...
Highly recommend to reserve in advanced as there is limited hourly seatings and desserts made upon order ( order more as u can’t do on the spot😉!) thanks delphine for the intro chat 💭 will be back!

image_desc: Photo by 🍀🌻🌸Juewee🌸🌻🍀 on August 02, 2020.
text:
🎀Take time out to think about an enjoyable occasion from your childhood - a birthday party or a trip to the zoo or making sandcastles on the beach. For a few moments let yourself be that child again.🎀 I didn’t read the quote of the day till I returned home from brunch. Coincidentally, I feel the joy of a child again today buying stuff children likes. 🤣 Today on my way to brunch, I chanced upon an ex-classmate’s fb account. We lost touched after Sec school but I remembered her as a fun loving person who took nice photos. So I was really happy that she is a photographer now! Omg! 🥰 I hope she will accept my FB friend invite as I would love to reconnect with her! Next, I found a pretty corner in the cafe that I went several times but did not notice. It’s a high bar table facing a wall with nicely hanged pictures. 🥰 I had a nice quiet moment with my ear plugs and ebook and delicious brunch. After that, I unknowingly walked into Chateraise and bought a big family cooler bag of 12 assorted ice-creams! Omg I’m not exactly an ice-cream person but I think I will like them. (Hubby might like them better!)🥰 Then, I went to Cold Storage to buy newly arrived pretty flowers and took the last box of Hersey’s Mint Creme Wafers off the shelf. This mint wafers are really nice if you are a mint person like me. 🥰 Finally, went to NTUC to buy my favourite SA Kromco Ruby Apples. These apples are not as hard as the New Zealand ones. Didn’t noticed the apples were 1-for-1 till a kind NTUC auntie pointed out to me at the self checked-out counter and urged me to get 1 more pack! Omg I simply love getting “1-for-1” offer! On my way to get the additional pack of apples, I saw my favourite Starbucks Caramel Latte stacked up in a new shelf! No wonder I couldn’t find it earlier. 🥰 Oh and I learnt to play my first song on my ukulele - You Are My Sunshine. 🥰 All very mundane stuffs but enough to make me happy on a Sunday. Next, I’m gonna try my best to bake a nice cake for my parents tonight. 🥰❤️ Happy Sunday!

image_desc: Photo by Noobwifepantry on August 01, 2020. May be an image of text that says 'AF BAKED SALMON'.
text:
•RECIPE• Bought a slab of salmon and decided to try baking it with some ingredients found at home. You know it's good when your LO keeps asking for another helping. The photos did not do the dish justice cos I took the pictures hastily as my friends were waiting for lunch. I love the outburst of flavour when we cut open the baking paper before serving. You can add some wine to enhance the flavour too! ===============================================
INGREDIENTS:
• 1 slab of salmon
• 1/2 potato, sliced thinly
• 1/2 onion, sliced thinly
• A few cherry tomato, halved
• 3 cloves garlic, minced
• 1 stalk coriander, minced finely
• Olive oil

METHOD:
1) Spread the potato, onion and lay salmon on top of 2 pc of baking paper
2) Add the cherry tomatoes, garlic and coriander. Drizzle a generous amount of olive oil on the fish
3) Seal up the fish in the baking paper
4) Place it in the AF for about 12 min at 200 degree celcius. 
5) Remove and cut open the baking paper. Serve hot.

text: Major respect to these people. I hope you go far.

来週の日曜日はシンガポール建国記念日〜今朝空から戦闘機の爆音がめちゃ近くに聞こえて、サービスヤードの方を見ると…あのパレードで良く観るヘリコプター3機が🇸🇬国旗を吊るしながら周るシーンが、我が家から見えるとは初めてです❗️凄い〜❗️ちなみに今朝はこちらの団地管理と代表の国議員Lawrence Wang氏が住民に挨拶を、ドアを開けた時少し驚きましたわ🤣 シンガポールプレイグランドの象徴”ドラゴン”を描いたリサイクルカップを貰いました〜ありがとう❣️丁度買い物に行く準備で下に降りたら…看板とお菓子も置いてましたわ🤣 今年は55年建国記念日、近くで”55”を国旗で並んだ団地が見えました👏👏👍👍.
.
皆さん良い週末を❣️.
.
下周日就是国庆日了！
早上听见战斗机飞过的轟隆声 太近了就走去阳台一看..
居然见到了吊着国旗的直升机飞过 😲
这还是初次见飞來这区呢！
今早有议员 登门沿访这区的组屋居民
开门见到的時候 有吓一下 😳 
收到了Recycle Cup 是印上了代表SG Olden Days之一的Dragon Playgrounds(By Autistic Artist Abundance Lim)
画的好漂亮 👍👏👏
剛好要出門下楼去～ 见各組屋單位的升降機前
擺放了零食或飲料包等 是让居民们自由添加分享或享用
以及填寫关怀和祝福傳遞給周圍的前缐工作人員～
👏👏👏 謝謝居民委員会的用心！
.
㊗️大家 周未愉快！.
.

image_desc: Photo by #SGB • All About Singapore in Jalan Besar, Singapore with @dailylife____saigon.
text:
👉🏻Menuju NDP 2020, ISTANA OPEN VIRTUAL TOUR! 🌟🌟
.
🌟Setiap tahun, terutama selama Hari Raya dan Hari Nasional, Istana membuka pintunya bagi publik untuk mengintip ke salah satu situs warisan tertua di Singapura. Namun, karena situasi pandemi, gerbang ke Istana tetap terkunci. Sebagai gantinya, National Day Istana Open House diadakan secara online tahun ini melalui platform Facebook dan Instagram Presiden Halimah Yacob pada 2 Agustus, mulai pukul 10 pagi. Dan semua diundang untuk menengok Istana secara virtual!🥰
.
✅Selain ada tur virtual sekitar Istana, ada juga preview National Museum's latest live interactive series "Zoom into History" dan juga the Asian Civilisations Museum's virtual galleries! Buat kamu yang penasaran, jangan lupa buka facebook jam 10 pagi waktu Singapura besok!🥰
.
💜Alih alih pameran udara yang mengesankan, parade militer, dan pertunjukan multikultural dan kembang api yang menakjubkan, tahun ini akan dirayakan dengan serba digital. Tanggal 9 agustus nanti akan dimulai dengan morning parade,  jet tempur F-15SG yang mengitari pulau, paduan suara virtual, hingga kembang api yang diatur di 10 wilayah sehingga bisa dinikmati dari rumah! 💗💗
.
👉🏻Ada yang pernah ke Singapore pas National Day? Share pengalaman kamu dooong!😜😜
.
📸Photo by: @dailylife____in.sg
.

text:
🌻Yesterday is a cancelled cheque; tomorrow is a promissory note; today is the only cash you have - so spend it wisely. 🌻 I like this quote! Let’s spend our precious long weekend wisely! It’s boring but I’m eating bread again because hubby says we have to finish the bread before it expires tomorrow. So I tried to find the most interesting way to eat it! Pairing my sliced bread with canned tuna, cheese and a special star fried egg using my new Daiso egg mould. It looks like I’m eating a lot of sandwiches but actually it’s just 4 slices of bread. Perception okay. 🤣 Oh I also placed in my all time favourite- Bourbon Ajisalon assorted rice crackers! This is my no 2 favourite Japanese titbits. My no 1 is the fried noodle chicken snack. ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️ What a filling brunch! 😋😋😋Happy Saturday! 🤩

image_desc: Photo by Don Quijote Spanish Restaurant on August 01, 2020.
text:
A lot of people ask why use Bone-In Angus Beef Rib Steak; well here’s why:

Bone is a poor conductor of heat, it takes longer for bone to heat up! So when you grill steaks with bone-in, the meat that is touching the bone winds up being less cooked and therefore having a smoother (buttery) texture, which when eaten with connected meat that is slightly further away, you get a lovely flavour and mouthfeel😋 YUM.

We know you want some, so get in touch with the LINK IN BIO  https://take.sg/s/6582186969 or get in touch with our Contact Button.

text:
Long weekends are for gathering with your loved ones over a hearty meal in a convivial atmosphere. Haven’t made any plans for the upcoming long weekend? Round up your squad (note: capped at five per table please) and take a gastronomic trip to Vietnam with us.⁠
⁠
Our chef has curated an extensive menu based on his personal travels in and around Vietnam, so expect to find a vast array of delights including some lesser-known rarities. Have you tried Vietnamese egg coffee? It’s sweet, creamy and it even comes with a cool backstory tied to it!

text:
来週の日曜日はシンガポール建国記念日、今年やっと🇸🇬を掛けられました👍 ドンキーで京都和菓子”蕎麦ぼうろ” をゲット、旦那氏も好きなお菓子で、久々に一緒に食べました〜京都は何回も訪ねましたが、旦那氏はまだ行った事が無いんです🤣 行くなら春か秋、ついでにドライブトリップで神戸から四国を巡る〜来年は行けるよう、早くコロナウィルスが收束するように🙏 .
.
Photo 3: 京都巡りはやはり自転車🚲特に鴨川沿いは一番好きなルート.
Photo 4: 下鴨神社⛩参りに良く寄る出町柳の飛石
Photo 5: 朝早く自転車で鴨川を通るのが大好き.
Photo 6: 好きな場所 祇園白川
Photo 7: 下鴨神社⛩の巫女さま

.
起个早想出门却下大雨
只好先做家务 这雷阵雨 来的快也去的快 
还沒到中午 己放晴见蓝天
找到另一本”幸福的便当”(上册）再阅读
沖壶茶搭配在Donki SG买的京都小吃”蕎麦ぼうろ”
(用蕎麦粉烘焙的花型饼干）这像花形状的京都伝統焼菓子叫「そばぼうろ」(Soba Bouro)。以蕎麦(Soba)粉、小麦粉、蛋和砂糖製成的烘饼。咬一口、在口中散發出淡淡的甜味。使用蕎麦粉、口感独特＋非常脆。Donki Sg 可以买到 $5.5 /1包.
